utes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  48→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  49→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  50→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  51→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  52→\n  53→INTERFACES:\n  54→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  55→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download, text message relay\n  56→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n  57→- File Service: validatePath, listDirectory, buildTree, readFile, searchFiles, writeFile\n  58→\n  59→TRAPS:\n  60→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  61→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  62→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  63→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  64→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n  65→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n  66→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n  67→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n  68→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n  69→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n  70→- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n  71→- F-010: file operations restricted to TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS (defaults: cwd, Desktop, Downloads, tmpdir)\n  72→- F-010: file download limited to 50MB for documents, 10MB for images\n  73→- F-010: binary files cannot be displayed as text\n  74→\n  75→DECISIONS:\n  76→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from s