{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313033056d8a53ec5e38c4388","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"id":"20260313033056d8a53ec5e38c4388","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce387e0153ff26dc5d13988f45ec8","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/011-ai-cli-proxy/plan.md","content":"# Technical Implementation Plan: F-011 AI CLI Proxy\n\n**Feature ID**: F-011\n**Feature Name**: AI CLI Proxy\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n**Status**: Draft\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\n### 1.1 Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Telegram Bot                             │\n│                    (src/bot/telegram.js)                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      AI CLI Service                              │\n│                (src/services/ai-cli-service.js)                  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐     │\n│  │  Process    │  │  Heartbeat   │  │  Stream             │     │\n│  │  Manager    │  │  Manager     │  │  Handler            │     │\n│  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │                    │                    │\n         ▼                    ▼                    ▼\n┌────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐\n│ Session Store  │  │ CodeBuddy       │  │ MarkdownV2           │\n│ (extended)     │  │ Adapter         │  │ Formatter            │\n│                │  │ (extended)      │  │                      │\n└────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                    │  CodeBuddy CLI  │\n                    │  (external)     │\n                    └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.2 Key Design Decisions\n\n| Decision ID | Description | Rationale |\n|-------------|-------------|-----------|\n| D-1 | Create separate `ai-cli-service.js` instead of modifying `chat-service.js` | Separation of concerns; AI CLI execution has different lifecycle than chat |\n| D-2 | Store active process info in `session-store.js` | Consistent with existing session management pattern |\n| D-3 | Use SIGTERM → SIGKILL graceful termination | Standard practice, prevents zombie processes |\n| D-4 | Implement MarkdownV2 formatter as pure utility | Reusable, testable, no side effects |\n| D-5 | Extend `/stop` command instead of creating new `/ai-stop` | Consistent user experience with existing pattern |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Component Design\n\n### 2.1 AI CLI Service (`src/services/ai-cli-service.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: Encapsulate AI CLI execution logic with process tracking, heartbeat, and interrupt support.\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- Execute CodeBuddy CLI with session context\n- Track active processes per session\n- Provide interrupt capability\n- Manage heartbeat progress notifications\n- Format and return results\n\n**Dependencies**:\n- `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` (extended)\n- `src/services/session-store.js` (extended)\n- `src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js` (new)\n- `src/config.js`\n\n**Interface**:\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n * @property {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n * @property {string} prompt - User prompt/input\n * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback (text: string) => void\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback (info: HeartbeatInfo) => void\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (status: string) => void\n * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Optional abort signal\n */\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionResult\n * @property {string} output - Final output text\n * @property {boolean} timedOut - Whether execution timed out\n * @property {boolean} interrupted - Whether execution was interrupted\n * @property {number} elapsedMs - Execution time in milliseconds\n * @property {number} exitCode - Process exit code (if completed)\n */\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} HeartbeatInfo\n * @property {number} elapsedMs - Elapsed time in milliseconds\n * @property {number} stdoutBytes - Bytes received so far\n * @property {string} status - Current status ('running', 'streaming')\n */\n\n/**\n * Execute AI CLI with session context and process tracking.\n * @param {AiCliExecutionOptions} options\n * @returns {Promise<AiCliExecutionResult>}\n */\nexport async function executeAiCli(options) {}\n\n/**\n * Interrupt running AI CLI task for a session.\n * @param {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n * @returns {{ ok: boolean, pid?: number, error?: string }}\n */\nexport function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {}\n\n/**\n * Check if AI CLI is running for a session.\n * @param {string} sessionId\n * @returns {boolean}\n */\nexport function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {}\n\n/**\n * Get active process info for a session.\n * @param {string} sessionId\n * @returns {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number } | null}\n */\nexport function getActiveProcessInfo(sessionId) {}\n```\n\n### 2.2 CodeBuddy Adapter Extensions (`src/adapters/codebuddy.js`)\n\n**Changes**:\n- Add `AbortSignal` support for cancellation\n- Return child process reference for external management\n- Expose process info (PID) during execution\n\n**Extended Interface**:\n```javascript\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} CodeBuddyOptions\n * @property {Function} [onStdoutChunk] - Stream chunk callback\n * @property {Function} [onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback\n * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Abort signal for cancellation\n * @property {Object} [processTracker] - Object to receive process reference\n */\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} CodeBuddyResult\n * @property {string} output - Output text\n * @property {number} exitCode - Exit code\n * @property {boolean} timedOut - Whether timed out\n * @property {boolean} interrupted - Whether interrupted by signal\n * @property {number} elapsedMs - Execution time\n */\n\nexport async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n  // Return extended result with process tracking\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 MarkdownV2 Formatter (`src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: Convert Markdown output to Telegram MarkdownV2 format.\n\n**Interface**:\n```javascript\n/**\n * Characters that need escaping in MarkdownV2.\n */\nconst ESCAPE_CHARS = ['_', '*', '[', ']', '(', ')', '~', '`', '>', '#', '+', '-', '=', '|', '{', '}', '.', '!'];\n\n/**\n * Escape text for Telegram MarkdownV2 format.\n * @param {string} text - Text to escape\n * @returns {string} Escaped text\n */\nexport function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {\n  // Escape all special characters\n}\n\n/**\n * Format code block for Telegram MarkdownV2.\n * @param {string} code - Code content\n * @param {string} [language] - Optional language identifier\n * @returns {string} Formatted code block\n */\nexport function formatCodeBlock(code, language = '') {\n  // ```language\\ncode\\n```\n  // Note: Inside code blocks, only ` and \\ need escaping\n}\n\n/**\n * Convert common Markdown to MarkdownV2.\n * Handles: code blocks, inline code, bold, italic, links.\n * @param {string} markdown - Input markdown\n * @returns {string} MarkdownV2 formatted text\n */\nexport function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {\n  // Parse and convert each element\n}\n\n/**\n * Split text into segments respecting code block boundaries.\n * Useful for splitting long messages.\n * @param {string} text - Text to split\n * @param {number} maxLength - Maximum length per segment\n * @returns {string[]} Array of segments\n */\nexport function splitRespectingCodeBlocks(text, maxLength = 4000) {}\n```\n\n### 2.4 Session Store Extensions (`src/services/session-store.js`)\n\n**New Fields**:\n```javascript\nclass SessionStore {\n  // ... existing fields ...\n  \n  /**\n   * Active AI CLI process tracking.\n   * Map<sessionKey, ProcessInfo>\n   * @type {Map<string, { pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number, childProcess: ChildProcess }>}\n   */\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n}\n```\n\n**New Methods**:\n```javascript\n/**\n * Get active AI CLI process info.\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @returns {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number, childProcess: ChildProcess } | null}\n */\ngetActiveProcess(sessionKey) {}\n\n/**\n * Set active AI CLI process.\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @param {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, childProcess: ChildProcess }} info\n */\nsetActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) {}\n\n/**\n * Update stdout bytes for active process.\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n * @param {number} bytes\n */\nupdateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) {}\n\n/**\n * Clear active process.\n * @param {string} sessionKey\n */\nclearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Interface Design\n\n### 3.1 Config Schema Extensions\n\n**File**: `src/config.js`\n\n**New Environment Variables**:\n```javascript\n// Add to schema\nconst schema = z.object({\n  // ... existing fields ...\n  \n  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(10000),\n  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(30000),\n  AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n});\n\n// Exported config additions\nexport const config = Object.freeze({\n  // ... existing fields ...\n  \n  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n  aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs: parsed.AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS,\n  aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs: parsed.AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS,\n  aiCliEnableHeartbeat: parseBoolean(parsed.AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT),\n});\n```\n\n### 3.2 Telegram Bot Integration\n\n**File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n\n**Changes to text message handler**:\n```javascript\n// In bot.on('text', ...) handler\n\n// Check if AI CLI is running for this session\nif (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n  await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n  return;\n}\n\n// Use ai-cli-service for execution\nconst result = await executeAiCli({\n  sessionId,\n  prompt: ctx.message.text,\n  hooks: {\n    onChunk: (text) => streamPublisher.push(text),\n    onHeartbeat: (info) => {\n      // Push heartbeat progress to user\n      ctx.reply(`⏳ 任务执行中... (${Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000)}s)`)\n        .catch(() => {});\n    },\n    onStatus: (status) => {\n      if (status === 'running') {\n        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n});\n\n// Format output with MarkdownV2\nconst formattedOutput = convertToMarkdownV2(result.output);\n\n// Handle result\nif (result.interrupted) {\n  await ctx.reply('⏹️ 任务已被中断。');\n} else if (result.timedOut) {\n  await ctx.reply(`⏰ 任务执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`);\n} else {\n  streamPublisher.setFinalText(formattedOutput);\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Stop Command Extension\n\n**File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`\n\n**Changes**:\n```javascript\nimport { interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning } from '../../../services/ai-cli-service.js';\nimport { stopPipeline } from '../../../services/pipeline-controller.js';\n\nexport async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n  const { params, reply, userId, sessionId } = handlerCtx;\n  \n  // First, check for AI CLI task\n  if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n    const result = interruptAiCli(sessionId);\n    \n    if (result.ok) {\n      await logAuditEntry({\n        userId,\n        action: 'stop-ai-cli',\n        params: { pid: result.pid },\n        result: 'success',\n        sessionId\n      });\n      \n      await reply(`✅ AI CLI 任务已中断 (PID: ${result.pid})。`);\n      return;\n    } else {\n      await reply(`❌ 中断失败: ${result.error}`);\n      return;\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Fall back to pipeline stop (existing logic)\n  // ... existing stop pipeline code ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Data Model\n\n### 4.1 Session Store Schema\n\n```javascript\n// ProcessInfo type\n{\n  pid: number,           // Process ID\n  startedAt: number,     // Timestamp when process started\n  stdoutBytes: number,   // Bytes received so far\n  childProcess: ChildProcess  // Reference to child process for termination\n}\n```\n\n### 4.2 Execution Result Schema\n\n```javascript\n// AiCliExecutionResult\n{\n  output: string,        // Final output text (MarkdownV2 formatted)\n  timedOut: boolean,     // True if timed out\n  interrupted: boolean,  // True if interrupted by user\n  elapsedMs: number,     // Total execution time\n  exitCode: number | null,  // Exit code (null if interrupted)\n  stderr: string         // Error output if any\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Heartbeat Info Schema\n\n```javascript\n// HeartbeatInfo\n{\n  elapsedMs: number,     // Elapsed time in ms\n  stdoutBytes: number,   // Bytes received\n  status: 'running' | 'streaming' | 'waiting'\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`\n```javascript\ndescribe('AiCliService', () => {\n  describe('executeAiCli', () => {\n    it('should execute CodeBuddy and return output');\n    it('should track active process in session store');\n    it('should call onChunk callback for streaming output');\n    it('should call onHeartbeat callback periodically');\n    it('should handle timeout correctly');\n    it('should handle abort signal');\n    it('should clean up process on completion');\n  });\n  \n  describe('interruptAiCli', () => {\n    it('should interrupt running process');\n    it('should return error if no process running');\n    it('should clean up session store after interrupt');\n  });\n  \n  describe('isAiCliRunning', () => {\n    it('should return true when process is active');\n    it('should return false when no process');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**File**: `tests/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.test.js`\n```javascript\ndescribe('MarkdownV2Formatter', () => {\n  describe('escapeMarkdownV2', () => {\n    it('should escape all special characters');\n    it('should handle empty string');\n    it('should handle text with no special chars');\n    it('should handle text with multiple special chars');\n  });\n  \n  describe('formatCodeBlock', () => {\n    it('should format code block without language');\n    it('should format code block with language');\n    it('should escape backticks inside code');\n  });\n  \n  describe('convertToMarkdownV2', () => {\n    it('should convert code blocks');\n    it('should convert inline code');\n    it('should convert bold text');\n    it('should convert italic text');\n    it('should convert links');\n    it('should handle nested formatting');\n    it('should preserve line breaks');\n  });\n  \n  describe('splitRespectingCodeBlocks', () => {\n    it('should not split inside code blocks');\n    it('should split at paragraph boundaries');\n    it('should respect maxLength');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `tests/integration/ai-cli-integration.test.js`\n```javascript\ndescribe('AI CLI Integration', () => {\n  it('should execute full flow: prompt → execute → stream → result');\n  it('should maintain context across multiple turns');\n  it('should handle /stop during execution');\n  it('should show heartbeat progress');\n  it('should format output correctly for Telegram');\n});\n```\n\n### 5.3 Test Helpers\n\n**File**: `tests/helpers/mock-codebuddy.js`\n```javascript\n/**\n * Mock CodeBuddy CLI for testing.\n * Simulates various scenarios: success, timeout, error, slow output.\n */\nexport function createMockCodeBuddy(options = {}) {\n  return {\n    simulateSuccess: (output) => { ... },\n    simulateTimeout: () => { ... },\n    simulateError: (exitCode, stderr) => { ... },\n    simulateSlowOutput: (chunks, interval) => { ... },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n- Add config fields\n- Create MarkdownV2 formatter utility\n- Extend session store with process tracking\n\n### Phase 2: Core Service (T-010 ~ T-029)\n- Create AI CLI service\n- Extend CodeBuddy adapter\n- Implement process tracking\n\n### Phase 3: Integration (T-030 ~ T-049)\n- Integrate with Telegram bot\n- Extend /stop command\n- Add heartbeat progress\n\n### Phase 4: Testing & Polish (T-050 ~ T-069)\n- Unit tests\n- Integration tests\n- Error handling refinement\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk ID | Description | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|---------|-------------|--------|------------|------------|\n| R-1 | Process becomes zombie after SIGTERM | High | Low | Implement SIGKILL after grace period (5s) |\n| R-2 | MarkdownV2 formatting breaks existing output | Medium | Medium | Comprehensive test suite, gradual rollout |\n| R-3 | Heartbeat messages spam user | Medium | Medium | Configurable interval, minimum 10s |\n| R-4 | Race condition in process tracking | High | Low | Use chat-queue for serialization |\n| R-5 | Memory leak from unreleased process refs | Medium | Low | Cleanup on process close, timeout, and session reset |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Rollback Plan\n\nIf issues arise:\n1. **Feature flag**: Set `AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT=false` to disable heartbeat\n2. **Fallback to chat-service**: The existing `chat-service.js` remains unchanged, can be used if needed\n3. **Process cleanup**: On restart, all tracked processes are cleared\n\n---\n\n## 9. Monitoring & Observability\n\n### 9.1 Metrics to Track\n- AI CLI execution duration (histogram)\n- AI CLI success/failure rate\n- Heartbeat delivery rate\n- Process interrupt frequency\n- Output size distribution\n\n### 9.2 Logging\n- Log process start with PID, sessionId, prompt length\n- Log process end with exit code, duration, output size\n- Log interrupts with reason\n- Log heartbeat events at debug level\n\n---\n\n## 10. Documentation Updates\n\n### 10.1 Files to Update\n- `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm`: Add F-011 entries to KEY_FILES, TRAPS, DECISIONS\n- `README.md`: Document new config options\n- `.env.example`: Add new environment variables\n\n### 10.2 New Documentation\n- `docs/ai-cli-proxy.md`: Feature documentation for users\n\n---\n\n## 11. User Story Mapping\n\n| User Story | Tasks |\n|------------|-------|\n| US-1: Natural Language Execution | T-010, T-011, T-012, T-030, T-031 |\n| US-2: Multi-turn Context | T-013 (uses existing session-store) |\n| US-3: Task Interrupt | T-014, T-015, T-032, T-033 |\n| US-4: Heartbeat Progress | T-004, T-016, T-034 |\n| US-5: Error Handling | T-017, T-035 |\n| US-6: Markdown Formatting | T-006, T-007, T-008, T-036 |\n"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":66276,"output_tokens":4568,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce383eccc5875defafa9a8dd8fbc3","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:32:12.341Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
