{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313033215daa6c18b211049d9","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"id":"20260313033215daa6c18b211049d9","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019ce38916d0ab30a31b5456b834d0c8","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/011-ai-cli-proxy/tasks.md","content":"# Task Breakdown: F-011 AI CLI Proxy\n\n**Feature ID**: F-011\n**Feature Name**: AI CLI Proxy\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n**Status**: Ready for Implementation\n\n---\n\n## Task Legend\n\n- `[ ]` - Pending\n- `[x]` - Completed\n- `[P]` - Can be parallelized\n- `[US-X]` - Maps to User Story X\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Setup & Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n\n### T-001: Add F-011 config fields to schema\n- **Goal**: Extend config schema with AI CLI specific settings\n- **Input**: config.js current state, F-011 requirements\n- **Output**: Updated src/config.js with new fields\n- **File**: `src/config.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS defaults to 10000\n  - AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS defaults to 30000\n  - AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT defaults to true\n  - All fields properly validated with zod\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: Infrastructure\n\n### T-002: [P] Update .env.example with new config\n- **Goal**: Document new environment variables\n- **Input**: T-001 config changes\n- **Output**: Updated .env.example\n- **File**: `.env.example`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - All new F-011 env vars documented\n  - Includes default values and descriptions\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: Infrastructure\n\n### T-003: [P] Extend session-store with process tracking\n- **Goal**: Add active process tracking to session store\n- **Input**: session-store.js current state\n- **Output**: Extended session-store.js with process methods\n- **File**: `src/services/session-store.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - getActiveProcess(sessionKey) returns process info or null\n  - setActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) stores process info\n  - updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) updates byte count\n  - clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) removes process entry\n  - clear(sessionKey) also clears active process\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3 (Task Interrupt)\n\n### T-004: [P] Create heartbeat manager utility\n- **Goal**: Create reusable heartbeat logic\n- **Input**: F-011 heartbeat requirements\n- **Output**: New heartbeat-manager.js utility\n- **File**: `src/utils/heartbeat-manager.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - startHeartbeat(callback, intervalMs) returns stop function\n  - Heartbeat only triggers after thresholdMs elapsed\n  - Stop function clears timer and resources\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-4 (Heartbeat Progress)\n\n### T-005: [P] Write unit tests for session-store extensions\n- **Goal**: Test process tracking methods\n- **Input**: T-003 implementation\n- **Output**: Test file for session-store F-011 features\n- **File**: `tests/services/session-store-f011.test.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Test getActiveProcess/setActiveProcess\n  - Test updateProcessBytes\n  - Test clearActiveProcess\n  - Test clear also clears process\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-006: Create MarkdownV2 formatter utility\n- **Goal**: Implement Telegram MarkdownV2 formatting\n- **Input**: Telegram MarkdownV2 spec\n- **Output**: New markdown-v2-formatter.js\n- **File**: `src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - escapeMarkdownV2() escapes all required chars\n  - formatCodeBlock() creates proper code blocks\n  - convertToMarkdownV2() handles common markdown elements\n  - splitRespectingCodeBlocks() splits without breaking code\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-6 (Markdown Formatting)\n\n### T-007: [P] Write unit tests for MarkdownV2 formatter\n- **Goal**: Test formatter edge cases\n- **Input**: T-006 implementation\n- **Output**: Test file for formatter\n- **File**: `tests/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.test.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Test all escape chars\n  - Test code block formatting\n  - Test nested formatting\n  - Test splitting edge cases\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-6\n\n### T-008: [P] Write fixtures for MarkdownV2 tests\n- **Goal**: Create test fixtures for formatter\n- **Input**: Various markdown examples\n- **Output**: Fixture files in tests/fixtures/\n- **File**: `tests/fixtures/markdown-v2/`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Input markdown files\n  - Expected output files\n  - Covers edge cases\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-6\n\n### T-009: Update runtime.prizm documentation\n- **Goal**: Document F-011 in prizm docs\n- **Input**: F-011 implementation plan\n- **Output**: Updated .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n- **File**: `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - KEY_FILES includes new files\n  - TRAPS includes F-011 entries\n  - DECISIONS has F-011 entry\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: Infrastructure\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Core Service (T-010 ~ T-029)\n\n### T-010: Create AI CLI service skeleton\n- **Goal**: Create ai-cli-service.js with basic structure\n- **Input**: F-011 architecture\n- **Output**: New ai-cli-service.js with interface\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Module exports: executeAiCli, interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning, getActiveProcessInfo\n  - JSDoc comments for all functions\n  - Imports dependencies\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-1 (Natural Language Execution)\n\n### T-011: Implement executeAiCli core logic\n- **Goal**: Implement main execution flow\n- **Input**: T-010 skeleton, codebuddy.js adapter\n- **Output**: Working executeAiCli function\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Spawns CodeBuddy process\n  - Tracks process in session store\n  - Returns proper result object\n  - Handles errors gracefully\n- **Complexity**: High\n- **US**: US-1, US-5\n\n### T-012: Implement streaming output handling\n- **Goal**: Add real-time output streaming\n- **Input**: T-011 implementation\n- **Output**: Stream handling in executeAiCli\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - onChunk callback receives text chunks\n  - Output accumulated correctly\n  - Byte count tracked for heartbeat\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-1\n\n### T-013: Implement session context preservation\n- **Goal**: Integrate with session-store for context\n- **Input**: T-011 implementation, session-store\n- **Output**: Context-aware execution\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Uses session-store.toPrompt() for context\n  - Appends user/assistant messages to history\n  - Respects MAX_HISTORY_TURNS\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-2 (Multi-turn Context)\n\n### T-014: Implement process interrupt mechanism\n- **Goal**: Add ability to interrupt running process\n- **Input**: T-011 implementation, session-store\n- **Output**: interruptAiCli function\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Finds process by session ID\n  - Sends SIGTERM, then SIGKILL after grace period\n  - Clears session store entry\n  - Returns proper result\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-015: Implement AbortSignal support\n- **Goal**: Support AbortSignal for cancellation\n- **Input**: T-011 implementation\n- **Output**: AbortSignal handling in executeAiCli\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Accepts signal in options\n  - Aborts when signal fires\n  - Cleans up resources properly\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-016: Implement heartbeat progress\n- **Goal**: Add heartbeat progress notification\n- **Input**: T-004 heartbeat-manager, T-011 implementation\n- **Output**: Heartbeat callbacks during execution\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Starts heartbeat after threshold\n  - Calls onHeartbeat with info object\n  - Stops heartbeat on completion/interrupt\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-4\n\n### T-017: Implement enhanced error handling\n- **Goal**: Provide user-friendly error messages\n- **Input**: T-011 implementation, error scenarios\n- **Output**: Comprehensive error handling\n- **File**: `src/services/ai-cli-service.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Process spawn failure → clear message\n  - Timeout → suggestion to use /stop or increase timeout\n  - Non-zero exit → include stderr in message\n  - Interrupt → indicate user interrupted\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-5\n\n### T-018: Extend CodeBuddy adapter for process tracking\n- **Goal**: Return process reference during execution\n- **Input**: codebuddy.js current state\n- **Output**: Extended runCodeBuddy with processTracker\n- **File**: `src/adapters/codebuddy.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Accepts processTracker option\n  - Sets processTracker.process = child during spawn\n  - Returns extended result with interrupted flag\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-019: [P] Write unit tests for AI CLI service - execution\n- **Goal**: Test executeAiCli function\n- **Input**: T-011, T-012 implementation\n- **Output**: Test file for ai-cli-service\n- **File**: `tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Test successful execution\n  - Test streaming output\n  - Test error handling\n  - Test timeout\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-1, US-5\n\n### T-020: [P] Write unit tests for AI CLI service - interrupt\n- **Goal**: Test interrupt functionality\n- **Input**: T-014, T-015 implementation\n- **Output**: Tests in ai-cli-service.test.js\n- **File**: `tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Test interruptAiCli success\n  - Test interrupt with no process\n  - Test AbortSignal abort\n  - Test SIGTERM → SIGKILL progression\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-021: [P] Write unit tests for AI CLI service - heartbeat\n- **Goal**: Test heartbeat functionality\n- **Input**: T-016 implementation\n- **Output**: Tests in ai-cli-service.test.js\n- **File**: `tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Test heartbeat starts after threshold\n  - Test heartbeat interval\n  - Test heartbeat stops on completion\n  - Test heartbeat with interrupt\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-4\n\n### T-022: [P] Create mock CodeBuddy for testing\n- **Goal**: Create test helper for mocking CLI\n- **Input**: Test requirements\n- **Output**: Mock helper in tests/helpers/\n- **File**: `tests/helpers/mock-codebuddy.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - simulateSuccess(output)\n  - simulateTimeout()\n  - simulateError(exitCode, stderr)\n  - simulateSlowOutput(chunks, interval)\n  - simulateInterruptible()\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: Testing Infrastructure\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Integration (T-030 ~ T-049)\n\n### T-030: Integrate AI CLI service with Telegram text handler\n- **Goal**: Use ai-cli-service in text message handler\n- **Input**: ai-cli-service, telegram.js\n- **Output**: Updated text handler with AI CLI\n- **File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Checks if AI CLI already running\n  - Calls executeAiCli with proper hooks\n  - Uses streamPublisher for real-time output\n  - Formats output with MarkdownV2\n- **Complexity**: High\n- **US**: US-1, US-2, US-6\n\n### T-031: Add onChunk streaming to Telegram\n- **Goal**: Wire up streaming output to Telegram\n- **Input**: T-030 implementation\n- **Output**: Real-time output in Telegram\n- **File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Chunks push to streamPublisher\n  - Editable message updates in real-time\n  - Respects flush interval and min chars\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-1\n\n### T-032: Extend /stop command for AI CLI tasks\n- **Goal**: Allow /stop to interrupt AI CLI\n- **Input**: stop.js handler, ai-cli-service\n- **Output**: Updated /stop handler\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Checks for AI CLI task first\n  - Calls interruptAiCli if running\n  - Falls back to pipeline stop if not\n  - Logs audit entry\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-033: Add permission check for AI CLI interrupt\n- **Goal**: Only allow task owner or admin to interrupt\n- **Input**: T-032 implementation, permission-guard\n- **Output**: Permission check in stop handler\n- **File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - User who started task can interrupt\n  - Admin can interrupt any task\n  - Others get permission denied\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-3\n\n### T-034: Add heartbeat progress to Telegram\n- **Goal**: Show heartbeat progress to user\n- **Input**: T-030, T-016 implementation\n- **Output**: Progress messages during long tasks\n- **File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Sends progress message with elapsed time\n  - Uses typing action for status\n  - Throttled to avoid spam\n  - Can be disabled via config\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-4\n\n### T-035: Add error messages with recovery suggestions\n- **Goal**: Show helpful error messages\n- **Input**: T-030, T-017 implementation\n- **Output**: User-friendly error handling\n- **File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Timeout error includes suggestion\n  - Process failure includes recovery steps\n  - Interrupt shows confirmation\n- **Complexity**: Low\n- **US**: US-5\n\n### T-036: Integrate MarkdownV2 formatting\n- **Goal**: Format all AI CLI output for Telegram\n- **Input**: T-006 formatter, T-030 implementation\n- **Output**: Properly formatted Telegram messages\n- **File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n- **Acceptance Criteria**:\n  - Code blocks render correctly\n  - Bold/italic work\n  - Links are clickable\n  - No formatting breakage\n- **Complexity**: Medium\n- **US**: US-6\n\n### T-037: Update help text for /stop command\n- **Goal**: Document AI CLI interrupt cap