 52, 193 (uses `sessionKey`)\n- Context snapshot `src/services/chat-service.js` lines 517-533 shows `buildSessionContext` that creates both `sessionId` and `sessionKey`\n\n**Description**: The documents use `sessionKey` but `spec.md` interface (lines 183-194) uses `sessionId` as parameter. The actual implementation uses `sessionKey` (format: `channel:sessionId`) internally but exposes `sessionId` externally.\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: `chat-service.js` shows `sessionKey = channel:sessionId` (line 532). `session-store.js` uses `sessionKey` internally.\n\n**Recommendation**: Standardize terminology across all documents. Either consistently use `sessionId` in interfaces with note about internal `sessionKey`, or clarify the distinction in spec.\n\n---\n\n#### MEDIUM-03: Missing Task for Existing Heartbeat Integration\n**Channel**: 覆盖缺口\n**Files**:\n- `tasks.md` - no task addresses `codebuddy.js` heartbeat modification\n- Context snapshot `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` lines 427-441 shows existing heartbeat for logging only\n\n**Description**: Tasks.md T-004 creates new `heartbeat-manager.js`, T-016 implements heartbeat in `ai-cli-service.js`, but no task explicitly modifies the existing heartbeat in `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` to integrate with the new user-facing heartbeat. The existing heartbeat only logs (line 438), it doesn't call any callback.\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: The existing `codebuddy.js` heartbeat (lines 427-441) only logs to `logger.info`. No callback mechanism exists.\n\n**Recommendation**: Add a task to extend `codebuddy.js` heartbeat to support callbacks, or clarify that `ai-cli-service.js` will implement its own heartbeat mechanism independent of the adapter's logging heartbeat.\n\n---\n\n#### MEDIUM-04: AC-3 Permission Check Ambiguity\n**Channel**: 歧义检测\n**Files**:\n- `spec.md` line 62: AC-3.3 says \"中断需要适当权限（admin 或当前任务发起者）\"\n- `tasks.md` T-033 defines acceptance criteria about permission checks\n- Context snapshot doesn't show any mechanism for tracking \"task initiator\"\n\n**Description**: AC-3.3 specifies that either admin OR \"current task initiator\" can interrupt. However, there's no task to implement tracking of who initiated a task. The `#activeProcessBySessionKey` schema only stores `{ pid, startedAt, stdoutBytes, childProcess }` - no `initiatorUserId` field.\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: Section 4 session-store.js extension schema (plan.md lines 225-228) doesn't include userId tracking.\n\n**Recommendation**: Add `initiatorUserId` to the process info schema and add a task to track this. Update T-003 acceptance criteria accordingly.\n\n---\n\n#### MEDIUM-05: Process Tracker Object Contract Undefined\n**Channel**: 歧义检测\n**Files**:\n- `plan.md` line 147: `processTracker` option mentioned\n- `plan.md` line 243: `processTracker.process = child during spawn`\n- No detailed contract in spec\n\n**Description**: The `processTracker` object's contract is only partially defined. What properties should it have? What happens if the caller doesn't provide it? Is it required for interrupt functionality?\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: `codebuddy.js` doesn't currently accept a `processTracker` option.\n\n**Recommendation**: Define full contract for `processTracker` object in spec interface section, including required/optional properties and behavior.\n\n---\n\n#### LOW-01: Missing Task for chat-service.js Integration Decision\n**Channel**: 不完整检测\n**Files**:\n- `plan.md` D-1: \"Create separate `ai-cli-service.js` instead of modifying `chat-service.js`\"\n- No task addresses whether `chat-service.js` should be deprecated or coexist\n\n**Description**: Decision D-1 creates a new service, but there's no task addressing the relationship with existing `chat-service.js`. Will `chat-service.js` be deprecated? Will both coexist? Will `chat-service.js` be refactored to use `ai-cli-service.js`?\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: `chat-service.js` currently uses `runCodeBuddy` directly (line 558).\n\n**Recommendation**: Add clarification task or document the coexistence strategy in plan.md.\n\n---\n\n#### LOW-02: Test File Count Summary Mismatch\n**Channel**: 不一致性\n**Files**:\n- `tasks.md` line 583-589 shows summary table\n\n**Description**: Summary table shows 44 tasks total, but counting the phases: Phase 1 (9) + Phase 2 (13) + Phase 3 (11) + Phase 4 (11) = 44. However, Phase 4 tasks are numbered T-050 ~ T-060 which is 11 tasks, but the task IDs listed are T-050 to T-060 = 11 tasks. The summary is correct but the task range in header says \"T-050 ~ T-069\".\n\n**Verification**: T-050 to T-060 = 11 tasks, not T-050 to T-069.\n\n**Recommendation**: Fix task range header in Phase 4 from \"T-050 ~ T-069\" to \"T-050 ~ T-060\".\n\n---\n\n#### LOW-03: Existing stop.js Session ID Parameter Not Documented\n**Channel**: 不一致性\n**Files**:\n- `tasks.md` T-032 line 348: expects `sessionId` in `handlerCtx`\n- Context snapshot `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` doesn't show `sessionId` in the handler context\n\n**Description**: T-032 expects `sessionId` to be available in `handlerCtx`, but the existing stop.js handler (as shown in context snapshot) doesn't appear to receive `sessionId`. This needs to be added as part of the task.\n\n**Verification against Section 4**: The stop.js excerpt shows `handlerCtx` destructuring but doesn't include `sessionId`.\n\n**Recommendation**: Clarify that T-032/T-033 should also add `sessionId` to the handler context, or verify this is already available from the command routing layer.\n\n---\n\n### Prizm Rules Alignment Check\n✅ No violations detected against `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm` RULES and PATTERNS:\n- Follows existing session management pattern\n- Follows existing command handler extension pattern\n- Follows existing utility creation pattern\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Level | Count |\n|-------|-------|\n| CRITICAL | 0 |\n| HIGH | 0 |\n| MEDIUM | 5 |\n| LOW | 3 |\n| **Total** | **8** |\n\n---\n\n### Verdict: **PASS WITH WARNINGS**\n\nNo CRITICAL or HIGH issues found. The documents are well-structured and consistent. The MEDIUM issues are quality improvements that should be addressed but don't block implementation:\n\n1. **MEDIUM-01**: Config naming overlap - needs clarification but not blocking\n2. **MEDIUM-02**: Terminology ambiguity - can be resolved during implementation\n3. **MEDIUM-03**: Missing task for adapter heartbeat - may be intentional design choice\n4. **MEDIUM-04**: Permission tracking gap - should be added for AC-3.3 compliance\n5. **MEDIUM-05**: Process tracker contract - can be defined during implementation\n\n**Recommendation**: Proceed to implementation. Consider addressing MEDIUM-04 (initiator tracking) before Phase 2 to ensure AC-3.3 compliance.\n\n---\n\n**COMPLETION_SIGNAL**: Phase 4 cross-check complete. Result: **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** (0 CRITICAL, 0 HIGH, 5 MEDIUM, 3 LOW)."}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":45050,"output_tokens":2147,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce38ad1fcbcc575dc63c55a10f158","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:35:14.183Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
