{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603130346028f136e41972c4173","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"id":"202603130346028f136e41972c4173","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The test is asserting `execResult.interrupted === true` but it's false. The issue is that when we interrupt via `interruptAiCli`, the cleanup runs which removes the process from session store, but the `interrupted` flag is not being set correctly because `interruptAiCli` doesn't communicate with the running `executeAiCli`.\n\nLet me fix this by having `interruptAiCli` set a flag that `executeAiCli` can check:</think>"}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce38bdd117b44f51df57146b62d27","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T19:46:05.955Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
