{"type":"user","uuid":"82db7f69-2135-46e2-8f2c-82b16dd7765c","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b8c82ee06f084c1c8b5d4692","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Context Snapshot: F-011 AI CLI Proxy\n   2→\n   3→## Section 1: Feature Brief\n   4→\n   5→### Feature Description\n   6→将 AI CLI（cbc/codebuddy）作为智能代理层，用户用自然语言描述意图，Bot 调用 AI CLI 来理解并执行复杂任务。这是 PrizmClaw 区别于普通远程 shell 工具的核心差异化能力。\n   7→\n   8→**交互模式**：用户发送自然语言消息（如'帮我重构 src/utils.js 里的 parseDate 函数'），Bot 将消息作为 prompt 传给 AI CLI，AI CLI 执行后将结果流式回传到 Telegram。支持多轮会话上下文保持（基于现有 CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO 和会话管理机制），用户可以连续追问或补充指令。\n   9→\n  10→**长任务支持**：AI CLI 执行可能耗时较长，需要心跳进度推送（CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS 配置），用户可通过 /stop 中断正在执行的 AI CLI 任务。\n  11→\n  12→**输出格式化**：AI CLI 的 Markdown 输出需适配 Telegram MarkdownV2 格式，代码块、链接等元素正确渲染。\n  13→\n  14→**与现有 CodeBuddy CLI 配置集成**：CODEBUDDY_BIN、CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG 等。\n  15→\n  16→### Acceptance Criteria\n  17→- AC-1: 用户发送自然语言指令，Bot 调用 AI CLI 执行并将结果回传到 Telegram\n  18→- AC-2: AI CLI 会话上下文在多轮对话中保持，用户可连续追问\n  19→- AC-3: 支持通过 /stop 中断正在执行的 AI CLI 任务\n  20→- AC-4: 长时间运行的 AI CLI 任务有心跳进度推送，用户不会感觉卡住\n  21→- AC-5: AI CLI 的 Markdown 输出正确适配 Telegram MarkdownV2 格式\n  22→- AC-6: AI CLI 进程异常退出或超时时返回可理解的错误信息与建议操作\n  23→\n  24→### Dependencies\n  25→- F-009: General Command Executor (completed)\n  26→\n  27→---\n  28→\n  29→## Section 2: Project Structure\n  30→\n  31→### src/ Directory\n  32→```\n  33→src/\n  34→├── adapters/\n  35→│   └── codebuddy.js          # AI CLI adapter (spawn process)\n  36→├── bot/\n  37→│   ├── commands/\n  38→│   │   ├── handlers/\n  39→│   │   │   ├── stop.js       # /stop command handler\n  40→│   │   │   ├── cd.js         # /cd command handler\n  41→│   │   │   ├── more.js       # /more command handler\n  42→│   │   │   └── ... (other handlers)\n  43→│   │   ├── index.js          # Command router\n  44→│   │   ├── parser.js         # Command parser\n  45→│   │   ├── registry.js       # Command registry\n  46→│   │   └── validator.js      # Command validator\n  47→│   └── telegram.js           # Main Telegram bot setup\n  48→├── http/\n  49→│   └── server.js\n  50→├── pipeline-infra/\n  51→│   ├── cli-entry.js\n  52→│   ├── config-loader.js\n  53→│   ├── error-codes.js\n  54→│   ├── index.js\n  55→│   ├── lock-manager.js\n  56→│   ├── path-policy.js\n  57→│   ├── script-runner.js\n  58→│   └── state-manager.js\n  59→├── routes/\n  60→│   └── api-routes.js\n  61→├── security/\n  62→│   ├── confirmation-manager.js\n  63→│   ├── guard.js\n  64→│   ├── param-sanitizer.js\n  65→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n  66→│   └── system-guard.js\n  67→├── services/\n  68→│   ├── audit-log-service.js\n  69→│   ├── chat-queue.js\n  70→│   ├── chat-service.js       # Chat with session context\n  71→│   ├── command-executor-service.js\n  72→│   ├── commit-service.js\n  73→│   ├── file-service.js\n  74→│   ├── git-service.js\n  75→│   ├── index.js\n  76→│   ├── log-pager.js\n  77→│   ├── output-pager-service.js\n  78→│   ├── pipeline-control-service.js\n  79→│   ├── pipeline-controller.js\n  80→│   ├── plan-ingestion-service.js\n  81→│   ├── realtime-hub.js\n  82→│   ├── screenshot-service.js\n  83→│   ├── session-store.js      # Session state management\n  84→│   ├── status-aggregator.js\n  85→│   ├── system-exec-service.js\n  86→│   └── telegram-pusher.js\n  87→├── utils/\n  88→│   ├── file-utils.js\n  89→│   └── logger.js\n  90→├── config.js                 # Main configuration\n  91→└── index.js                  # Entry point\n  92→```\n  93→\n  94→### tests/ Directory\n  95→```\n  96→tests/\n  97→├── bot/\n  98→├── config/\n  99→├── fixtures/\n 100→├── helpers/\n 101→│   ├── fixture-loader.js\n 102→│   ├── mock-runner.js\n 103→│   ├── mock-telegram.js\n 104→│   └── test-state.js\n 105→├── integration/\n 106→├── pipeline-infra/\n 107→├── runtime/\n 108→├── security/\n 109→├── services/\n 110→│   ├── command-executor-service.test.js\n 111→│   ├── output-pager-service.test.js\n 112→│   ├── session-store-f009.test.js\n 113→│   ├── system-exec-service-f009.test.js\n 114→│   └── ...\n 115→└── utils/\n 116→```\n 117→\n 118→---\n 119→\n 120→## Section 3: Prizm Context\n 121→\n 122→### root.prizm\n 123→```\n 124→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n 125→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n 126→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n 127→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n 128→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n 129→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n 130→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n 131→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n 132→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n 133→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n 134→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n 135→\n 136→MODULE_INDEX:\n 137→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n 138→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n 139→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n 140→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n 141→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n 142→\n 143→LOAD_RULES:\n 144→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n 145→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n 146→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n 147→\n 148→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n 149→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n 150→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n 151→```\n 152→\n 153→### runtime.prizm\n 154→```\n 155→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n 156→MODULE: runtime\n 157→PATH: src/**\n 158→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n 159→\n 160→ENTRYPOINT:\n 161→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n 162→\n 163→KEY_FILES:\n 164→- src/config.js\n 165→- src/http/server.js\n 166→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n 167→- src/services/chat-service.js\n 168→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n 169→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n 170→- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n 171→- src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 172→- src/services/output-pager-service.js\n 173→- src/services/file-service.js\n 174→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n 175→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n 176→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n 177→- src/bot/telegram.js\n 178→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n 179→- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 180→- src/bot/commands/handlers/cd.js\n 181→- src/bot/commands/handlers/more.js\n 182→- src/bot/commands/handlers/ls.js\n 183→- src/bot/commands/handlers/tree.js\n 184→- src/bot/commands/handlers/cat.js\n 185→- src/bot/commands/handlers/head.js\n 186→- src/bot/commands/handlers/tail.js\n 187→- src/bot/commands/handlers/find.js\n 188→- src/bot/commands/handlers/upload.js\n 189→- src/bot/commands/handlers/download.js\n 190→- src/security/permission-guard.js\n 191→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n 192→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n 193→- src/security/system-guard.js\n 194→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n 195→- src/utils/file-utils.js\n 196→\n 197→SUBDIRS:\n 198→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n 199→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n 200→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n 201→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n 202→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n 203→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n 204→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n 205→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n 206→\n 207→INTERFACES:\n 208→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n 209→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /cd, /more, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, /commit, /commits, /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download, text message relay\n 210→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService, SystemGuard\n 211→- File Service: validatePath, listDirectory, buildTree, readFile, searchFiles, writeFile\n 212→\n 213→TRAPS:\n 214→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n 215→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n 216→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n 217→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n 218→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n 219→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n 220→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n 221→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n 222→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n 223→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n 224→- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n 225→- F-010: file operations restricted to TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS (defaults: cwd, Desktop, Downloads, tmpdir)\n 226→- F-010: file download limited to 50MB for documents, 10MB for images\n 227→- F-010: binary files cannot be displayed as text\n 228→\n 229→DECISIONS:\n 230→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n 231→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n 232→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n 233→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n 234→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f006 | add security guard layer with permission tiers, param sanitization, confirmation flow, and audit logging\n 235→- 2026-03-14 | runtime-f007 | add test infrastructure with fixtures, helpers (mock-runner, mock-telegram, test-state, fixture-loader), and layered test execution\n 236→- 2026-03-15 | runtime-f008 | add commit workflow with /commit, /commits commands, pre-commit validation, session tracking, and audit logging\n 237→- 2026-03-16 | runtime-f009 | add general command executor with blacklist, high-risk keywords, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination, and /cd /more commands\n 238→- 2026-03-13 | runtime-f009 | add general command executor with blacklist, high-risk keyword detection, confirmation flow, session cwd, output pagination, /cd and /more commands\n 239→- 2026-03-13 | runtime-f010 | add file manager with /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download commands, path validation, and file operations\n 240→```\n 241→\n 242→---\n 243→\n 244→## Section 4: Existing Source Files\n 245→\n 246→### src/config.js\n 247→```javascript\n 248→import 'dotenv/config';\n 249→import { z } from 'zod';\n 250→\n 251→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from './pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n 252→import { resolveDaemonLogPaths } from './pipeline-infra/path-policy.js';\n 253→\n 254→const schema = z.object({\n 255→  TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 256→  ENABLE_TELEGRAM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 257→  ALLOWED_USER_IDS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 258→  CODEBUDDY_BIN: z.string().min(1).default('codebuddy'),\n 259→  CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG: z.string().default('-y'),\n 260→  CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 261→  CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(15000),\n 262→  TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 263→  TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 264→  REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(120000),\n 265→  MAX_PROMPT_CHARS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8000),\n 266→  MAX_HISTORY_TURNS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n 267→  WEB_HOST: z.string().default('127.0.0.1'),\n 268→  WEB_PORT: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(8787),\n 269→  ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n 270→  ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 271→  SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n 272→  LOG_LEVEL: z.enum(['fatal', 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug', 'trace', 'silent']).default('info'),\n 273→  // F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 274→  USER_PERMISSIONS: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 275→  ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 276→  AUDIT_LOG_DIR: z.string().optional().default('logs'),\n 277→  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n 278→  AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(5),\n 279→  // F-009: General Command Executor\n 280→  COMMAND_BLACKLIST: z.string().optional().default(''),\n 281→  HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS: z.string().optional().default('rm -rf,sudo,kill,chmod -R,chown,dd,mkfs,shutdown,reboot,halt'),\n 282→  DIRECT_EXEC_MODE: z.string().optional().default('false'),\n 283→  // F-010: File Manager\n 284→  FILE_MAX_READ_SIZE: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(1048576), // 1MB\n 285→  FILE_MAX_TREE_DEPTH: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(3),\n 286→  FILE_MAX_TREE_ITEMS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n 287→  FILE_MAX_SEARCH_DEPTH: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(10),\n 288→  FILE_MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\n 289→  FILE_SEARCH_RESULTS_PER_PAGE: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(20)\n 290→});\n 291→\n 292→const parsed = schema.parse(process.env);\n 293→\n 294→function parseAllowedUserIds(input) {\n 295→  return new Set(\n 296→    input\n 297→      .split(',')\n 298→      .map((id) => id.trim())\n 299→      .filter(Boolean)\n 300→  );\n 301→}\n 302→\n 303→function parseCsvList(input) {\n 304→  return input\n 305→    .split(',')\n 306→    .map((item) => item.trim())\n 307→    .filter(Boolean);\n 308→}\n 309→\n 310→function parseBoolean(input) {\n 311→  const normalized = (input ?? '').trim().toLowerCase();\n 312→  return normalized === '1' || normalized === 'true' || normalized === 'yes' || normalized === 'on';\n 313→}\n 314→\n 315→function parseUserPermissions(input) {\n 316→  const permissions = new Map();\n 317→  if (!input || !input.trim()) {\n 318→    return permissions;\n 319→  }\n 320→\n 321→  const entries = input.split(',').map((s) => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);\n 322→  for (const entry of entries) {\n 323→    const [userId, role] = entry.split(':').map((s) => s.trim());\n 324→    if (userId && role) {\n 325→      const normalizedRole = role.toLowerCase();\n 326→      if (['admin', 'operator', 'viewer'].includes(normalizedRole)) {\n 327→        permissions.set(userId, normalizedRole);\n 328→      }\n 329→    }\n 330→  }\n 331→  return permissions;\n 332→}\n 333→\n 334→const enableTelegram = parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_TELEGRAM);\n 335→if (enableTelegram && !parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN) {\n 336→  throw new Error('ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true 时必须提供 TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN');\n 337→}\n 338→\n 339→const pipelineInfra = loadPipelineInfraConfig({\n 340→  env: process.env,\n 341→  argv: process.argv.slice(2),\n 342→  cwd: process.cwd()\n 343→});\n 344→\n 345→const daemonLogPaths = resolveDaemonLogPaths(pipelineInfra.projectRoot);\n 346→\n 347→export const config = Object.freeze({\n 348→  telegramBotToken: parsed.TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN,\n 349→  enableTelegram,\n 350→  allowedUserIds: parseAllowedUserIds(parsed.ALLOWED_USER_IDS),\n 351→  codebuddyBin: parsed.CODEBUDDY_BIN,\n 352→  codebuddyPermissionFlag: parsed.CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG,\n 353→  codebuddyEchoStdio: parseBoolean(parsed.CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO),\n 354→  codebuddyHeartbeatMs: parsed.CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS,\n 355→  telegramFileAllowedRoots: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS),\n 356→  telegramFileCandidateDirs: parseCsvList(parsed.TELEGRAM_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS),\n 357→  requestTimeoutMs: parsed.REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS,\n 358→  maxPromptChars: parsed.MAX_PROMPT_CHARS,\n 359→  maxHistoryTurns: parsed.MAX_HISTORY_TURNS,\n 360→  webHost: parsed.WEB_HOST,\n 361→  webPort: parsed.WEB_PORT,\n 362→  enableSystemExec: parseBoolean(parsed.ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC),\n 363→  allowedCommandPrefixes: parseCsvList(parsed.ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES),\n 364→  systemExecTimeoutMs: parsed.SYSTEM_EXEC_TIMEOUT_MS,\n 365→  logLevel: parsed.LOG_LEVEL,\n 366→  userPermissions: parseUserPermissions(parsed.USER_PERMISSIONS),\n 367→  allowAdminSkipConfirm: parseBoolean(parsed.ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM),\n 368→  auditLogDir: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_DIR,\n 369→  auditLogMaxSizeMb: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB,\n 370→  auditLogMaxFiles: parsed.AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES,\n 371→  commandBlacklist: parseCsvList(parsed.COMMAND_BLACKLIST),\n 372→  highRiskKeywords: parseCsvList(parsed.HIGH_RISK_KEYWORDS),\n 373→  directExecMode: parseBoolean(parsed.DIRECT_EXEC_MODE),\n 374→  fileMaxReadSize: parsed.FILE_MAX_READ_SIZE,\n 375→  fileMaxTreeDepth: parsed.FILE_MAX_TREE_DEPTH,\n 376→  fileMaxTreeItems: parsed.FILE_MAX_TREE_ITEMS,\n 377→  fileMaxSearchDepth: parsed.FILE_MAX_SEARCH_DEPTH,\n 378→  fileMaxSearchResults: parsed.FILE_MAX_SEARCH_RESULTS,\n 379→  fileSearchResultsPerPage: parsed.FILE_SEARCH_RESULTS_PER_PAGE,\n 380→  pipelineInfra: Object.freeze({\n 381→    ...pipelineInfra,\n 382→    daemonLogPaths\n 383→  })\n 384→});\n 385→```\n 386→\n 387→### src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n 388→```javascript\n 389→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n 390→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 391→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n 392→\n 393→function writeEcho(tag, text) {\n 394→  const normalized = String(text ?? '');\n 395→  if (!normalized) {\n 396→    return;\n 397→  }\n 398→\n 399→  const lines = normalized.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n 400→  for (const line of lines) {\n 401→    if (!line) {\n 402→      continue;\n 403→    }\n 404→    process.stdout.write(`[CodeBuddy:${tag}] ${line}\\n`);\n 405→  }\n 406→}\n 407→\n 408→export async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n 409→  const { onStdoutChunk } = options;\n 410→  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n 411→\n 412→  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n 413→    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n 414→  }\n 415→\n 416→  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n 417→    const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n 418→      stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n 419→    });\n 420→\n 421→    const startedAt = Date.now();\n 422→    logger.info({ pid: child.pid, bin: config.codebuddyBin, args }, 'CodeBuddy process started');\n 423→\n 424→    let stdout = '';\n 425→    let stderr = '';\n 426→\n 427→    const heartbeat =\n 428→      config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs > 0\n 429→        ? setInterval(() => {\n 430→            const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n 431→            logger.info(\n 432→              {\n 433→                pid: child.pid,\n 434→                elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000),\n 435→                stdoutBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stdout),\n 436→                stderrBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stderr)\n 437→              },\n 438→              'CodeBuddy still running'\n 439→            );\n 440→          }, config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs)\n 441→        : null;\n 442→\n 443→    const timeout =\n 444→      config.requestTimeoutMs > 0\n 445→        ? setTimeout(() => {\n 446→            child.kill('SIGTERM');\n 447→            reject(new Error(`CodeBuddy 执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）`));\n 448→          }, config.requestTimeoutMs)\n 449→        : null;\n 450→\n 451→    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n 452→      const text = chunk.toString();\n 453→      stdout += text;\n 454→\n 455→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n 456→        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n 457→      }\n 458→\n 459→      if (typeof onStdoutChunk === 'function') {\n 460→        onStdoutChunk(text);\n 461→      }\n 462→    });\n 463→\n 464→    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n 465→      const text = chunk.toString();\n 466→      stderr += text;\n 467→\n 468→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n 469→        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n 470→      }\n 471→    });\n 472→\n 473→    child.on('error', (err) => {\n 474→      if (timeout) {\n 475→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n 476→      }\n 477→      if (heartbeat) {\n 478→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n 479→      }\n 480→      reject(new Error(`无法启动 CodeBuddy: ${err.message}`));\n 481→    });\n 482→\n 483→    child.on('close', (code) => {\n 484→      if (timeout) {\n 485→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n 486→      }\n 487→      if (heartbeat) {\n 488→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n 489→      }\n 490→\n 491→      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n 492→      logger.info(\n 493→        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000) },\n 494→        'CodeBuddy process closed'\n 495→      );\n 496→\n 497→      if (code === 0) {\n 498→        resolve(stdout.trim() || 'CodeBuddy 未返回文本结果。');\n 499→        return;\n 500→      }\n 501→\n 502→      reject(\n 503→        new Error(`CodeBuddy 退出码 ${code}。${stderr ? `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}` : ''}`)\n 504→      );\n 505→    });\n 506→  });\n 507→}\n 508→```\n 509→\n 510→### src/services/chat-service.js\n 511→```javascript\n 512→import { runCodeBuddy } from '../adapters/codebuddy.js';\n 513→import { sanitizeInput } from '../security/guard.js';\n 514→import { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\n 515→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n 516→\n 517→export function buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId) {\n 518→  const normalizedChannel = String(channel ?? '').trim();\n 519→  const normalizedSessionId = String(sessionId ?? '').trim();\n 520→\n 521→  if (!normalizedChannel) {\n 522→    throw new Error('channel 不能为空。');\n 523→  }\n 524→\n 525→  if (!normalizedSessionId) {\n 526→    throw new Error('sessionId 不能为空。');\n 527→  }\n 528→\n 529→  return {\n 530→    channel: normalizedChannel,\n 531→    sessionId: normalizedSessionId,\n 532→    sessionKey: `${normalizedChannel}:${normalizedSessionId}`\n 533→  };\n 534→}\n 535→\n 536→export async function chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks = {} }) {\n 537→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n 538→\n 539→  return chatQueue.run(session.sessionKey, async () => {\n 540→    const sanitized = sanitizeInput(message);\n 541→\n 542→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n 543→      stage: 'accepted',\n 544→      channel: session.channel,\n 545→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n 546→    });\n 547→\n 548→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'user', sanitized);\n 549→\n 550→    const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(session.sessionKey, session.channel);\n 551→\n 552→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n 553→      stage: 'running',\n 554→      channel: session.channel,\n 555→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n 556→    });\n 557→\n 558→    const reply = await runCodeBuddy(prompt, {\n 559→      onStdoutChunk: (text) => {\n 560→        realtimeHooks.onAssistantChunk?.({\n 561→          text,\n 562→          channel: session.channel,\n 563→          sessionId: session.sessionId\n 564→        });\n 565→      }\n 566→    });\n 567→\n 568→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'assistant', reply);\n 569→\n 570→    realtimeHooks.onAssistantDone?.({\n 571→      reply,\n 572→      channel: session.channel,\n 573→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n 574→    });\n 575→\n 576→    return reply;\n 577→  });\n 578→}\n 579→\n 580→export function resetSession({ channel, sessionId }) {\n 581→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n 582→  sessionStore.clear(session.sessionKey);\n 583→}\n 584→```\n 585→\n 586→### src/services/session-store.js\n 587→```javascript\n 588→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 589→\n 590→class SessionStore {\n 591→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 592→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 593→  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n 594→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n 595→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n 596→  // F-010: File search results state for pagination\n 597→  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n 598→\n 599→  get(sessionKey) {\n 600→    if (!this.#messagesBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n 601→      this.#messagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n 602→    }\n 603→    return this.#messagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n 604→  }\n 605→\n 606→  append(sessionKey, role, content) {\n 607→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n 608→    messages.push({ role, content });\n 609→\n 610→    const maxMessages = config.maxHistoryTurns * 2;\n 611→    if (messages.length > maxMessages) {\n 612→      messages.splice(0, messages.length - maxMessages);\n 613→    }\n 614→  }\n 615→\n 616→  clear(sessionKey) {\n 617→    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 618→    this.#commitsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 619→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 620→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 621→    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 622→  }\n 623→\n 624→  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel = 'unknown') {\n 625→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n 626→\n 627→    return [\n 628→      `你正在通过 ${channel} 渠道提供电脑助手服务。`,\n 629→      '请使用自然、简洁、可执行的表达。',\n 630→      '如果用户请求系统操作或截图，明确说明步骤与结果。',\n 631→      '当你产出本地文件（截图/文档）时，必须额外输出独立行：SEND_FILE:<绝对路径>。',\n 632→      '禁止仅输出 @image:xxx 或相对路径；路径必须是绝对路径（例如 /var/folders/... 或 /home/...）。',\n 633→      '以下是最近对话上下文：',\n 634→      ...messages.map((msg) => `${msg.role === 'user' ? '用户' : '助手'}: ${msg.content}`),\n 635→      '请继续回答最后一条用户消息。'\n 636→    ].join('\\n');\n 637→  }\n 638→\n 639→  addCommit(sessionKey, commitInfo) {\n 640→    if (!this.#commitsBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n 641→      this.#commitsBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n 642→    }\n 643→    const commits = this.#commitsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n 644→    commits.push({\n 645→      ...commitInfo,\n 646→      timestamp: commitInfo.timestamp || Date.now()\n 647→    });\n 648→  }\n 649→\n 650→  getCommits(sessionKey) {\n 651→    return this.#commitsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || [];\n 652→  }\n 653→\n 654→  getLastCommit(sessionKey) {\n 655→    const commits = this.getCommits(sessionKey);\n 656→    return commits.length > 0 ? commits[commits.length - 1] : null;\n 657→  }\n 658→\n 659→  getCwd(sessionKey) {\n 660→    return this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n 661→  }\n 662→\n 663→  setCwd(sessionKey, cwd) {\n 664→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, cwd);\n 665→  }\n 666→\n 667→  getOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n 668→    return this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n 669→  }\n 670→\n 671→  setOutputPages(sessionKey, pages) {\n 672→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, pages);\n 673→  }\n 674→\n 675→  clearOutputPages(sessionKey) {\n 676→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 677→  }\n 678→\n 679→  getSearchResults(sessionKey) {\n 680→    return this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n 681→  }\n 682→\n 683→  setSearchResults(sessionKey, results) {\n 684→    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, results);\n 685→  }\n 686→\n 687→  clearSearchResults(sessionKey) {\n 688→    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 689→  }\n 690→}\n 691→\n 692→export const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n 693→```\n 694→\n 695→### src/bot/telegram.js (excerpts - key parts for F-011)\n 696→```javascript\n 697→// Key constants\n 698→const TELEGRAM_MSG_CHUNK_SIZE = 3800;\n 699→const STREAM_MIN_CHARS = 220;\n 700→const STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS = 1200;\n 701→const TYPING_INTERVAL_MS = 3500;\n 702→\n 703→// Stream publisher for real-time output\n 704→function createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx) {\n 705→  let fullText = '';\n 706→  let renderedText = '';\n 707→  let pendingChars = 0;\n 708→  let lastFlushAt = 0;\n 709→  let flushChain = Promise.resolve();\n 710→  let activeMessage = null;\n 711→  let activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n 712→  let publishedMessageCount = 0;\n 713→\n 714→  async function ensureActiveMessage() {\n 715→    if (activeMessage) {\n 716→      return;\n 717→    }\n 718→    activeMessage = await ctx.reply('处理中...');\n 719→    activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n 720→    publishedMessageCount += 1;\n 721→  }\n 722→\n 723→  async function render(force = false) {\n 724→    const now = Date.now();\n 725→\n 726→    if (!force && pendingChars < STREAM_MIN_CHARS && now - lastFlushAt < STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS) {\n 727→      return;\n 728→    }\n 729→\n 730→    if (fullText === renderedText) {\n 731→      pendingChars = 0;\n 732→      return;\n 733→    }\n 734→\n 735→    await ensureActiveMessage();\n 736→\n 737→    const segments = splitMessage(fullText);\n 738→    const targetLastIndex = Math.max(segments.length - 1, 0);\n 739→\n 740→    while (activeSegmentIndex < targetLastIndex) {\n 741→      const text = segments[activeSegmentIndex] ?? ' ';\n 742→      await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, text);\n 743→\n 744→      activeMessage = await ctx.reply('继续输出中...');\n 745→      activeSegmentIndex += 1;\n 746→      publishedMessageCount += 1;\n 747→    }\n 748→\n 749→    const activeText = segments[targetLastIndex] ?? ' ';\n 750→    await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, activeText);\n 751→\n 752→    renderedText = fullText;\n 753→    pendingChars = 0;\n 754→    lastFlushAt = now;\n 755→  }\n 756→\n 757→  function enqueueRender(force = false) {\n 758→    flushChain = flushChain.then(() => render(force));\n 759→  }\n 760→\n 761→  return {\n 762→    push(text) {\n 763→      const appendText = text ?? '';\n 764→      if (!appendText) {\n 765→        return;\n 766→      }\n 767→      fullText += appendText;\n 768→      pendingChars += appendText.length;\n 769→      enqueueRender(false);\n 770→    },\n 771→    setFinalText(text) {\n 772→      fullText = text ?? '';\n 773→      pendingChars = Math.max(pendingChars, STREAM_MIN_CHARS);\n 774→      enqueueRender(true);\n 775→    },\n 776→    async finish() {\n 777→      enqueueRender(true);\n 778→      await flushChain;\n 779→      return {\n 780→        outputLength: renderedText.length,\n 781→        messageCount: publishedMessageCount\n 782→      };\n 783→    }\n 784→  };\n 785→}\n 786→\n 787→// Text message handler (key part for AI CLI integration)\n 788→bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n 789→  // Check for pipeline commands first\n 790→  const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n 791→  if (handled) {\n 792→    return;\n 793→  }\n 794→\n 795→  const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n 796→  const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n 797→\n 798→  // ... direct exec mode handling ...\n 799→\n 800→  let typingTimer = null;\n 801→\n 802→  try {\n 803→    ensureAllowed(ctx);\n 804→    await ctx.sendChatAction('typing');\n 805→\n 806→    const streamPublisher = createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx);\n 807→    typingTimer = setInterval(() => {\n 808→      ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n 809→    }, TYPING_INTERVAL_MS);\n 810→\n 811→    const reply = await chatWithSession({\n 812→      channel: 'telegram',\n 813→      sessionId,\n 814→      message: ctx.message.text,\n 815→      realtimeHooks: {\n 816→        onStatus: ({ stage }) => {\n 817→          if (stage === 'running') {\n 818→            ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n 819→          }\n 820→        },\n 821→        onAssistantChunk: ({ text }) => {\n 822→          streamPublisher.push(text);\n 823→        }\n 824→      }\n 825→    });\n 826→\n 827→    // Handle file markers and final text...\n 828→  } catch (error) {\n 829→    // Error handling...\n 830→  } finally {\n 831→    if (typingTimer) {\n 832→      clearInterval(typingTimer);\n 833→    }\n 834→  }\n 835→});\n 836→```\n 837→\n 838→### src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n 839→```javascript\n 840→import { stopPipeline } from '../../../services/pipeline-controller.js';\n 841→import { logAuditEntry } from '../../../services/audit-log-service.js';\n 842→import {\n 843→  createConfirmation,\n 844→  checkConfirmation as _checkConfirmation,\n 845→  confirmAction,\n 846→  cancelConfirmation\n 847→} from '../../../security/confirmation-manager.js';\n 848→import { sanitizeParam } from '../../../security/param-sanitizer.js';\n 849→import { isAdmin } from '../../../security/permission-guard.js';\n 850→\n 851→const pendingConfirmations = new Map();\n 852→\n 853→export const stopMeta = {\n 854→  name: 'stop',\n 855→  aliases: [],\n 856→  description: '停止运行中的管道',\n 857→  usage: '/stop [target]',\n 858→  examples: ['/stop', '/stop my-feature'],\n 859→  params: [\n 860→    {\n 861→      name: 'target',\n 862→      type: 'string',\n 863→      required: false,\n 864→      description: '目标标识符'\n 865→    }\n 866→  ],\n 867→  requiresAuth: true,\n 868→  minRole: 'admin',\n 869→  helpText: '/stop [target] - 停止运行中的管道'\n 870→};\n 871→\n 872→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 873→  const { params, reply, userId, userRole: _userRole, requiresConfirmation, parsed } = handlerCtx;\n 874→\n 875→  // ... confirmation flow logic ...\n 876→\n 877→  try {\n 878→    const result = await stopPipeline({ type: pipelineType });\n 879→\n 880→    if (result.ok) {\n 881→      await logAuditEntry({\n 882→        userId,\n 883→        action: 'stop',\n 884→        params: { type: pipelineType },\n 885→        result: 'success'\n 886→      });\n 887→      // ... success message ...\n 888→    } else {\n 889→      // ... failure message ...\n 890→    }\n 891→  } catch (error) {\n 892→    // ... error handling ...\n 893→  }\n 894→}\n 895→```\n 896→\n 897→### src/services/command-executor-service.js\n 898→```javascript\n 899→import { config } from '../config.js';\n 900→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n 901→import { executeSystemCommand } from './system-exec-service.js';\n 902→import { checkCommandBlacklist, detectHighRiskKeywords } from '../security/system-guard.js';\n 903→import { createConfirmation, confirmAction } from '../security/confirmation-manager.js';\n 904→import { logAuditEntry } from './audit-log-service.js';\n 905→import { paginateOutput, storeOutputPages, hasMorePages } from './output-pager-service.js';\n 906→import { getUserRole } from '../security/permission-guard.js';\n 907→\n 908→export async function executeCommand(options) {\n 909→  const { command, sessionId, userId, skipConfirmation = false, confirmationId } = options;\n 910→\n 911→  // Check blacklist first\n 912→  const blacklistResult = checkCommandBlacklist(command, config.commandBlacklist);\n 913→  if (blacklistResult.blocked) {\n 914→    await logAuditEntry({\n 915→      userId,\n 916→      role: getUserRole(userId),\n 917→      action: 'exec',\n 918→      params: { command },\n 919→      result: 'denied',\n 920→      reason: `Blacklisted command: ${blacklistResult.matchedCommand}`,\n 921→      sessionId\n 922→    });\n 923→\n 924→    throw new Error(`命令被拒绝：${blacklistResult.reason}`);\n 925→  }\n 926→\n 927→  // Detect high-risk keywords\n 928→  const riskResult = detectHighRiskKeywords(command, config.highRiskKeywords);\n 929→\n 930→  // If high-risk and not confirmed, require confirmation\n 931→  if (riskResult.isHighRisk && !skipConfirmation && !confirmationId) {\n 932→    const params = { command, sessionId };\n 933→    const { confirmId, message } = createConfirmation(userId, 'exec', params);\n 934→\n 935→    await logAuditEntry({\n 936→      userId,\n 937→      role: getUserRole(userId),\n 938→      action: 'exec',\n 939→      params: { command },\n 940→      result: 'pending_confirmation',\n 941→      reason: `High-risk keywords: ${riskResult.detectedKeywords.join(', ')}`,\n 942→      sessionId\n 943→    });\n 944→\n 945→    return {\n 946→      needsConfirmation: true,\n 947→      confirmationId: confirmId,\n 948→      confirmationMessage: message,\n 949→      detectedKeywords: riskResult.detectedKeywords\n 950→    };\n 951→  }\n 952→\n 953→  // ... execution logic ...\n 954→\n 955→  const cwd = sessionStore.getCwd(sessionId) || process.cwd();\n 956→  const result = await executeSystemCommand(command, { cwd });\n 957→  const output = formatOutput(result);\n 958→  const pages = paginateOutput(output);\n 959→  const displayOutput = pages[0];\n 960→\n 961→  if (pages.length > 1) {\n 962→    storeOutputPages(sessionId, pages.slice(1));\n 963→  }\n 964→\n 965→  return {\n 966→    stdout: result.stdout,\n 967→    stderr: result.stderr,\n 968→    exitCode: result.exitCode,\n 969→    timedOut: result.timedOut,\n 970→    output: displayOutput,\n 971→    hasMorePages: hasMorePages(sessionId),\n 972→    needsConfirmation: false\n 973→  };\n 974→}\n 975→```\n 976→\n 977→---\n 978→\n 979→## Section 5: Existing Tests\n 980→\n 981→### tests/services/command-executor-service.test.js\n 982→```javascript\n 983→// Tests for F-009 command executor service\n 984→// Covers: blacklist, high-risk detection, confirmation flow, execution, pagination\n 985→```\n 986→\n 987→### tests/services/output-pager-service.test.js\n 988→```javascript\n 989→// Tests for F-009 output pagination\n 990→// Covers: paginateOutput, storeOutputPages, getNextPage, hasMorePages\n 991→```\n 992→\n 993→### tests/services/session-store-f009.test.js\n 994→```javascript\n 995→// Tests for F-009 session store extensions\n 996→// Covers: getCwd, setCwd, getOutputPages, setOutputPages\n 997→```\n 998→\n 999→### tests/services/system-exec-service-f009.test.js\n1000→```javascript\n1001→// Tests for F-009 system exec service enhancements\n1002→// Covers: timeout handling, SIGTERM/SIGKILL grace period\n1003→```\n1004→\n1005→---\n1006→\n1007→## Key Observations for F-011\n1008→\n1009→1. **Existing AI CLI Integration**: The `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` already spawns CodeBuddy CLI with streaming support via `onStdoutChunk` callback.\n1010→\n1011→2. **Session Management**: `session-store.js` maintains conversation history with `toPrompt()` method for multi-turn context.\n1012→\n1013→3. **Stream Publishing**: `telegram.js` has `createEditableStreamPublisher` for real-time Telegram output with message editing.\n1014→\n1015→4. **Heartbeat**: `codebuddy.js` has heartbeat logging via `CODEBUDDY_HEARTBEAT_MS` config, but no user-facing notification.\n1016→\n1017→5. **Stop Mechanism**: Current `/stop` only stops pipelines, not CodeBuddy processes. Need to extend for AI CLI task interruption.\n1018→\n1019→6. **Telegram Formatting**: No MarkdownV2 formatting exists. Current `sendMessageChunked` uses `'Markdown'` parse_mode.\n1020→\n1021→7. **Missing Features for F-011**:\n1022→   - Process tracking for AI CLI tasks (PID storage per session)\n1023→   - Ability to interrupt running CodeBuddy process\n1024→   - Telegram MarkdownV2 formatter\n1025→   - Heartbeat progress notification to user\n1026→   - Better error messages with recovery suggestions\n1027→\n1028→---\n1029→\n1030→## Implementation Log\n1031→\n1032→**Completed**: 2026-03-13\n1033→\n1034→### Files Created\n1035→\n1036→1. **`src/services/ai-cli-service.js`** - New AI CLI service with:\n1037→   - `executeAiCli()` - Main execution with process tracking, streaming, heartbeat\n1038→   - `interruptAiCli()` - Interrupt running AI CLI task\n1039→   - `isAiCliRunning()` - Check if AI CLI is running\n1040→   - `getActiveProcessInfo()` - Get process info\n1041→\n1042→2. **`src/utils/heartbeat-manager.js`** - Reusable heartbeat utility:\n1043→   - `startHeartbeat()` - Start heartbeat with threshold and interval\n1044→   - `createHeartbeatManager()` - Lifecycle-based heartbeat manager\n1045→\n1046→3. **`src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js`** - Telegram MarkdownV2 formatter:\n1047→   - `escapeMarkdownV2()` - Escape special characters\n1048→   - `formatCodeBlock()` - Format code blocks\n1049→   - `formatInlineCode()` - Format inline code\n1050→   - `convertToMarkdownV2()` - Convert common Markdown\n1051→   - `splitRespectingCodeBlocks()` - Split without breaking code blocks\n1052→\n1053→4. **`tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`** - Comprehensive tests for AI CLI service\n1054→5. **`tests/services/session-store-f011.test.js`** - Tests for session store extensions\n1055→6. **`tests/config/f011-config.test.js`** - Tests for F-011 config fields\n1056→7. **`tests/utils/heartbeat-manager.test.js`** - Tests for heartbeat manager\n1057→8. **`tests/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.test.js`** - Tests for MarkdownV2 formatter\n1058→\n1059→### Files Modified\n1060→\n1061→1. **`src/config.js`** - Added F-011 config fields:\n1062→   - `AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS` (default: 10000)\n1063→   - `AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS` (default: 30000)\n1064→   - `AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT` (default: true)\n1065→\n1066→2. **`src/services/session-store.js`** - Added process tracking:\n1067→   - `#activeProcessBySessionKey` private field\n1068→   - `getActiveProcess()`, `setActiveProcess()`, `updateProcessBytes()`, `clearActiveProcess()`\n1069→   - Extended `clear()` to also clear active process\n1070→\n1071→3. **`src/services/index.js`** - Exported ai-cli-service functions\n1072→\n1073→4. **`src/bot/telegram.js`** - Integrated AI CLI service:\n1074→   - Import `executeAiCli`, `interruptAiCli`, `isAiCliRunning`, `convertToMarkdownV2`\n1075→   - Text handler now uses `executeAiCli()` instead of `chatWithSession()`\n1076→   - Added check for running AI CLI before starting new task\n1077→   - Added heartbeat progress notification\n1078→   - `/reset` now interrupts running AI CLI task\n1079→\n1080→5. **`src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`** - Extended for AI CLI:\n1081→   - Import AI CLI service functions\n1082→   - Check for AI CLI task first before pipeline stop\n1083→   - Updated help text to mention AI CLI tasks\n1084→\n1085→6. **`.env.example`** - Added F-011 environment variables documentation\n1086→\n1087→7. **`.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm`** - Updated with F-011:\n1088→   - Added `ai-cli-service.js`, `heartbeat-manager.js`, `markdown-v2-formatter.js` to KEY_FILES\n1089→   - Added F-011 TRAPS\n1090→   - Added F-011 DECISIONS entry\n1091→\n1092→### Key Decisions\n1093→\n1094→1. **Separate AI CLI Service**: Created `ai-cli-service.js` rather than modifying `chat-service.js` for separation of concerns\n1095→\n1096→2. **Process Tracking in Session Store**: Consistent with existing session management pattern\n1097→\n1098→3. **SIGTERM → SIGKILL Graceful Termination**: Standard practice, prevents zombie processes with 5s grace period\n1099→\n1100→4. **MarkdownV2 as Pure Utility**: Reusable, testable, no side effects\n1101→\n1102→5. **Extend /stop for AI CLI**: Consistent user experience with existing pattern\n1103→\n1104→6. **Heartbeat with Threshold**: Avoids spam for short-running tasks; only starts after threshold\n1105→\n1106→### Deviations from Plan\n1107→\n1108→1. **T-008 (MarkdownV2 fixtures)**: Skipped - tests cover edge cases adequately without separate fixture files\n1109→\n1110→2. **T-022 (Mock CodeBuddy)**: Skipped - using real codebuddy CLI for integration tests; mock not needed for current test coverage\n1111→\n1112→3. **T-039, T-040 (Integration tests)**: Deferred - existing unit tests provide sufficient coverage; can be added later\n1113→\n1114→### Test Results\n1115→\n1116→- All F-011 specific tests pass (66 tests)\n1117→- Pre-existing baseline failures remain (22 tests) - unrelated to F-011 implementation\n1118→- Tests cover: config, session store, heartbeat manager, MarkdownV2 formatter, AI CLI service\n1119→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3a32437d4af704548a467fd4021","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:00:55.294Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
