{"type":"user","uuid":"b09c5e1a-fee8-4275-9441-b4ab84ca3703","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_08b12708b49b454d81816efa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# PrizmClaw\n   2→\n   3→Telegram Bot Bridge for CodeBuddy CLI with Web API.\n   4→\n   5→## Features\n   6→\n   7→### AI CLI Proxy (F-011)\n   8→\n   9→PrizmClaw acts as an intelligent proxy layer for AI CLI tools. Users can interact with AI capabilities through natural language messages via Telegram.\n  10→\n  11→- **Natural Language Execution**: Send messages to execute AI-powered tasks\n  12→- **Multi-turn Conversation**: Context is preserved across multiple messages\n  13→- **Task Interrupt**: Use `/stop` to interrupt long-running tasks\n  14→- **Heartbeat Progress**: Progress notifications for long-running operations\n  15→- **MarkdownV2 Formatting**: Output is properly formatted for Telegram\n  16→\n  17→### Command Executor (F-009)\n  18→\n  19→Execute system commands safely with:\n  20→- Command blacklist\n  21→- High-risk keyword detection\n  22→- Confirmation flow for dangerous operations\n  23→- Output pagination with `/more`\n  24→\n  25→### File Manager (F-010)\n  26→\n  27→Browse and manage files remotely:\n  28→- `/ls`, `/tree` - List directories\n  29→- `/cat`, `/head`, `/tail` - View file contents\n  30→- `/find` - Search for files\n  31→- `/upload`, `/download` - Transfer files\n  32→\n  33→### Pipeline Control (F-001, F-002, F-003)\n  34→\n  35→Manage development pipelines:\n  36→- `/pipeline`, `/bugfix`, `/planner` - Start pipelines\n  37→- `/status` - Check pipeline status\n  38→- `/logs` - View pipeline logs\n  39→- `/stop` - Stop running pipelines\n  40→\n  41→## Configuration\n  42→\n  43→### Environment Variables\n  44→\n  45→```bash\n  46→# Telegram\n  47→ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true\n  48→TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-bot-token\n  49→ALLOWED_USER_IDS=12345678,99887766\n  50→\n  51→# CodeBuddy CLI\n  52→CODEBUDDY_BIN=codebuddy\n  53→CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG=-y\n  54→CODEBUDDY_ECHO_STDIO=true\n  55→\n  56→# AI CLI Proxy (F-011)\n  57→AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS=10000\n  58→AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS=30000\n  59→AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT=true\n  60→\n  61→# Web Server\n  62→WEB_HOST=127.0.0.1\n  63→WEB_PORT=8787\n  64→\n  65→# Permissions\n  66→USER_PERMISSIONS=123456789:admin,987654321:operator\n  67→```\n  68→\n  69→### Permission Roles\n  70→\n  71→- `admin` - Full access to all commands\n  72→- `operator` - Can execute most commands, high-risk operations require confirmation\n  73→- `viewer` - Read-only access (status, logs)\n  74→\n  75→## Usage\n  76→\n  77→### Telegram Commands\n  78→\n  79→```\n  80→/start          - Start the bot\n  81→/help           - Show help message\n  82→/reset          - Reset session context\n  83→/stop           - Stop running task or pipeline\n  84→/status         - Show pipeline status\n  85→/logs           - View pipeline logs\n  86→\n  87→# File Operations\n  88→/ls [path]      - List directory\n  89→/tree [path]    - Show directory tree\n  90→/cat <path>     - View file contents\n  91→/find <pattern> - Search for files\n  92→\n  93→# Pipeline Control\n  94→/pipeline       - Run feature pipeline\n  95→/bugfix         - Run bugfix pipeline\n  96→/planner        - Run planner pipeline\n  97→/retry <id>     - Retry failed target\n  98→```\n  99→\n 100→### Natural Language Messages\n 101→\n 102→Simply send a text message to interact with the AI CLI:\n 103→\n 104→```\n 105→User: Help me refactor the parseDate function in src/utils.js\n 106→Bot: [AI processes and responds with suggestions]\n 107→```\n 108→\n 109→For multi-turn conversations:\n 110→\n 111→```\n 112→User: Create a new utility file for date parsing\n 113→Bot: [Creates file and shows result]\n 114→User: Now add timezone support to it\n 115→Bot: [Remembers context and adds timezone support]\n 116→```\n 117→\n 118→## Development\n 119→\n 120→### Prerequisites\n 121→\n 122→- Node.js 18+\n 123→- npm\n 124→\n 125→### Setup\n 126→\n 127→```bash\n 128→# Install dependencies\n 129→npm install\n 130→\n 131→# Copy environment file\n 132→cp .env.example .env\n 133→\n 134→# Edit configuration\n 135→vim .env\n 136→\n 137→# Run tests\n 138→npm test\n 139→\n 140→# Start server\n 141→npm start\n 142→```\n 143→\n 144→### Running Tests\n 145→\n 146→```bash\n 147→# Run all tests\n 148→npm test\n 149→\n 150→# Run specific test file\n 151→node --test tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js\n 152→\n 153→# Run integration tests\n 154→node --test tests/integration/ai-cli-telegram.test.js\n 155→```\n 156→\n 157→## Architecture\n 158→\n 159→```\n 160→src/\n 161→├── adapters/           # External service adapters\n 162→│   └── codebuddy.js    # CodeBuddy CLI adapter\n 163→├── bot/                # Telegram bot\n 164→│   ├── commands/       # Command handlers\n 165→│   └── telegram.js     # Bot setup and message handling\n 166→├── security/           # Security modules\n 167→│   ├── permission-guard.js\n 168→│   ├── param-sanitizer.js\n 169→│   └── confirmation-manager.js\n 170→├── services/           # Core services\n 171→│   ├── ai-cli-service.js   # F-011: AI CLI execution\n 172→│   ├── session-store.js    # Session management\n 173→│   └── ...\n 174→├── utils/              # Utilities\n 175→│   ├── markdown-v2-formatter.js  # F-011: Telegram formatting\n 176→│   ├── heartbeat-manager.js      # F-011: Heartbeat utility\n 177→│   └── logger.js\n 178→└── config.js           # Configuration\n 179→```\n 180→\n 181→## License\n 182→\n 183→MIT\n 184→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3a32437d4af704548a467fd4021","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:09:29.147Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
