{"type":"user","uuid":"9885c511-73e3-4b3a-a539-b25c818bb0aa","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3bc5266a17a3b9f417aa170e45f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Feature Specification: F-011 AI CLI Proxy\n   2→\n   3→**Feature ID**: F-011\n   4→**Feature Name**: AI CLI Proxy\n   5→**Slug**: 011-ai-cli-proxy\n   6→**Status**: Draft\n   7→**Created**: 2026-03-13\n   8→**Dependencies**: F-009 (General Command Executor - Completed)\n   9→\n  10→---\n  11→\n  12→## 1. Overview\n  13→\n  14→### 1.1 Description\n  15→将 AI CLI（cbc/codebuddy）作为智能代理层，用户用自然语言描述意图，Bot 调用 AI CLI 来理解并执行复杂任务。这是 PrizmClaw 区别于普通远程 shell 工具的核心差异化能力。\n  16→\n  17→### 1.2 Problem Statement\n  18→- 用户需要记住复杂的命令行参数和语法\n  19→- 简单任务需要多步操作，用户体验不流畅\n  20→- 缺乏智能化的任务理解和执行能力\n  21→- 长时间运行的任务缺乏进度反馈\n  22→\n  23→### 1.3 Goals\n  24→- 提供自然语言接口，降低使用门槛\n  25→- 支持多轮对话上下文保持\n  26→- 提供任务中断能力\n  27→- 实时进度反馈\n  28→- 正确的输出格式化\n  29→\n  30→---\n  31→\n  32→## 2. User Stories\n  33→\n  34→### US-1: 自然语言任务执行\n  35→**作为** 用户\n  36→**我想要** 用自然语言描述我的意图\n  37→**以便于** AI CLI 理解并执行复杂任务，无需记忆命令语法\n  38→\n  39→**验收标准**:\n  40→- AC-1.1: 用户发送自然语言消息后，Bot 调用 AI CLI 执行\n  41→- AC-1.2: 执行结果流式回传到 Telegram\n  42→- AC-1.3: 支持代码块、链接等 Markdown 元素正确渲染\n  43→\n  44→### US-2: 多轮对话上下文\n  45→**作为** 用户\n  46→**我想要** 在多轮对话中保持上下文\n  47→**以便于** 连续追问或补充指令，无需重复描述背景\n  48→\n  49→**验收标准**:\n  50→- AC-2.1: 会话上下文在多轮对话中保持\n  51→- AC-2.2: 用户可以追问或补充指令\n  52→- AC-2.3: 上下文根据 MAX_HISTORY_TURNS 配置自动裁剪\n  53→\n  54→### US-3: 任务中断\n  55→**作为** 用户\n  56→**我想要** 能够中断正在执行的 AI CLI 任务\n  57→**以便于** 在发现错误或改变主意时停止执行\n  58→\n  59→**验收标准**:\n  60→- AC-3.1: 提供 /stop 命令中断正在执行的 AI CLI 任务\n  61→- AC-3.2: 中断后返回确认消息\n  62→- AC-3.3: 中断需要适当权限（admin 或当前任务发起者）\n  63→\n  64→### US-4: 长任务进度反馈\n  65→**作为** 用户\n  66→**我想要** 在长时间运行的任务中看到进度反馈\n  67→**以便于** 知道任务正在执行，系统没有卡住\n  68→\n  69→**验收标准**:\n  70→- AC-4.1: 超过 HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS 的任务定期推送进度\n  71→- AC-4.2: 进度消息显示已执行时间和状态\n  72→- AC-4.3: 进度消息可配置（频率、内容）\n  73→\n  74→### US-5: 错误处理与恢复建议\n  75→**作为** 用户\n  76→**我想要** 在 AI CLI 异常时获得清晰的错误信息\n  77→**以便于** 了解问题原因并采取正确的恢复操作\n  78→\n  79→**验收标准**:\n  80→- AC-5.1: 进程异常退出时返回可理解的错误信息\n  81→- AC-5.2: 超时时返回超时提示和建议操作\n  82→- AC-5.3: 提供恢复建议（如重试、检查配置等）\n  83→\n  84→### US-6: Markdown 格式适配\n  85→**作为** 用户\n  86→**我想要** AI CLI 的 Markdown 输出正确渲染\n  87→**以便于** 在 Telegram 中看到格式良好的代码块、链接等\n  88→\n  89→**验收标准**:\n  90→- AC-6.1: 代码块使用 Telegram MarkdownV2 格式\n  91→- AC-6.2: 链接、粗体、斜体等元素正确转义\n  92→- AC-6.3: 特殊字符正确处理\n  93→\n  94→---\n  95→\n  96→## 3. Scope\n  97→\n  98→### 3.1 In Scope\n  99→- 扩展现有 `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` 支持进程跟踪和中断\n 100→- 新增 `src/services/ai-cli-service.js` 封装 AI CLI 调用逻辑\n 101→- 新增 `src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js` 处理 Telegram MarkdownV2 格式\n 102→- 扩展 `session-store.js` 存储活动进程信息\n 103→- 扩展 `/stop` 命令支持 AI CLI 任务中断\n 104→- 新增心跳进度推送机制\n 105→- 错误处理增强\n 106→\n 107→### 3.2 Out of Scope\n 108→- AI CLI 本身的功能修改（仅作为调用方）\n 109→- Web API 端点的 AI CLI 集成（仅 Telegram）\n 110→- 多 AI CLI 后端支持\n 111→- 流式输出的自定义配置（使用现有机制）\n 112→\n 113→---\n 114→\n 115→## 4. Functional Requirements\n 116→\n 117→### FR-1: AI CLI 执行服务\n 118→- FR-1.1: 提供 `executeAiCli(sessionId, prompt, options)` 方法\n 119→- FR-1.2: 支持流式输出回调\n 120→- FR-1.3: 支持心跳进度回调\n 121→- FR-1.4: 支持进程中断\n 122→- FR-1.5: 集成现有配置（CODEBUDDY_BIN, CODEBUDDY_PERMISSION_FLAG 等）\n 123→\n 124→### FR-2: 进程管理\n 125→- FR-2.1: 记录每个 session 的活动进程 PID\n 126→- FR-2.2: 支持通过 session ID 查找和终止进程\n 127→- FR-2.3: 进程退出后清理记录\n 128→\n 129→### FR-3: 心跳进度\n 130→- FR-3.1: 配置项 `AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS`（默认 10000）\n 131→- FR-3.2: 配置项 `AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS`（默认 30000）\n 132→- FR-3.3: 心跳消息包含：已执行时间、输出字节数、状态\n 133→\n 134→### FR-4: Telegram MarkdownV2 格式化\n 135→- FR-4.1: 转义特殊字符：`_`, `*`, `[`, `]`, `(`, `)`, `~`, `` ` ``, `>`, `#`, `+`, `-`, `=`, `|`, `{`, `}`, `.`, `!`\n 136→- FR-4.2: 代码块使用 ```language ... ``` 格式\n 137→- FR-4.3: 处理嵌套格式\n 138→\n 139→### FR-5: 错误处理\n 140→- FR-5.1: 进程启动失败 → \"无法启动 AI CLI，请检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置\"\n 141→- FR-5.2: 执行超时 → \"任务执行超时，可使用 /stop 中断或等待更长时间\"\n 142→- FR-5.3: 非零退出码 → \"任务异常退出，退出码: X，错误信息: ...\"\n 143→- FR-5.4: 用户中断 → \"任务已被用户中断\"\n 144→\n 145→---\n 146→\n 147→## 5. Non-Functional Requirements\n 148→\n 149→### NFR-1: 性能\n 150→- NFR-1.1: 流式输出延迟 < 500ms\n 151→- NFR-1.2: 心跳不影响主流程性能\n 152→\n 153→### NFR-2: 可靠性\n 154→- NFR-2.1: 进程中断后资源正确释放\n 155→- NFR-2.2: 异常情况不导致 Bot 崩溃\n 156→\n 157→### NFR-3: 可配置性\n 158→- NFR-3.1: 所有阈值可通过环境变量配置\n 159→- NFR-3.2: 心跳可禁用\n 160→\n 161→---\n 162→\n 163→## 6. Interface Design\n 164→\n 165→### 6.1 AI CLI Service API\n 166→```javascript\n 167→// src/services/ai-cli-service.js\n 168→\n 169→/**\n 170→ * Execute AI CLI with session context.\n 171→ * @param {Object} options\n 172→ * @param {string} options.sessionId - Session identifier\n 173→ * @param {string} options.prompt - User prompt\n 174→ * @param {Object} [options.hooks]\n 175→ * @param {Function} [options.hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback\n 176→ * @param {Function} [options.hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback\n 177→ * @param {Function} [options.hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback\n 178→ * @returns {Promise<{ output: string, timedOut: boolean, interrupted: boolean }>}\n 179→ */\n 180→export async function executeAiCli(options) {}\n 181→\n 182→/**\n 183→ * Interrupt running AI CLI task for a session.\n 184→ * @param {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n 185→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, pid?: number, error?: string }}\n 186→ */\n 187→export function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {}\n 188→\n 189→/**\n 190→ * Check if AI CLI is running for a session.\n 191→ * @param {string} sessionId\n 192→ * @returns {boolean}\n 193→ */\n 194→export function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {}\n 195→```\n 196→\n 197→### 6.2 MarkdownV2 Formatter API\n 198→```javascript\n 199→// src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js\n 200→\n 201→/**\n 202→ * Escape text for Telegram MarkdownV2 format.\n 203→ * @param {string} text\n 204→ * @returns {string}\n 205→ */\n 206→export function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {}\n 207→\n 208→/**\n 209→ * Format code block for Telegram.\n 210→ * @param {string} code\n 211→ * @param {string} [language]\n 212→ * @returns {string}\n 213→ */\n 214→export function formatCodeBlock(code, language) {}\n 215→\n 216→/**\n 217→ * Convert common Markdown to MarkdownV2.\n 218→ * @param {string} markdown\n 219→ * @returns {string}\n 220→ */\n 221→export function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {}\n 222→```\n 223→\n 224→### 6.3 Config Extensions\n 225→```javascript\n 226→// New config fields in src/config.js\n 227→{\n 228→  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n 229→  aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs: 10000,  // AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS\n 230→  aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs: 30000,   // AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS\n 231→  aiCliEnableHeartbeat: true,        // AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT\n 232→}\n 233→```\n 234→\n 235→---\n 236→\n 237→## 7. Data Model\n 238→\n 239→### 7.1 Session Store Extensions\n 240→```javascript\n 241→// session-store.js extensions for F-011\n 242→\n 243→class SessionStore {\n 244→  // ... existing fields ...\n 245→  \n 246→  // F-011: Active AI CLI process tracking\n 247→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map(); // sessionKey -> { pid, startedAt, stdoutBytes }\n 248→  \n 249→  getActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n 250→    return this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n 251→  }\n 252→  \n 253→  setActiveProcess(sessionKey, processInfo) {\n 254→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, processInfo);\n 255→  }\n 256→  \n 257→  clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n 258→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n 259→  }\n 260→}\n 261→```\n 262→\n 263→---\n 264→\n 265→## 8. Test Strategy\n 266→\n 267→### 8.1 Unit Tests\n 268→- `ai-cli-service.test.js`: Service logic, process management\n 269→- `markdown-v2-formatter.test.js`: Formatting, escaping\n 270→\n 271→### 8.2 Integration Tests\n 272→- `ai-cli-integration.test.js`: Full flow with mock CodeBuddy\n 273→- `ai-cli-stop.test.js`: Interrupt functionality\n 274→\n 275→### 8.3 Test Cases\n 276→- TC-1: Normal execution with streaming output\n 277→- TC-2: Multi-turn conversation context preservation\n 278→- TC-3: /stop interrupts running task\n 279→- TC-4: Heartbeat progress notification\n 280→- TC-5: Timeout handling\n 281→- TC-6: Process crash handling\n 282→- TC-7: MarkdownV2 formatting edge cases\n 283→\n 284→---\n 285→\n 286→## 9. Risks and Mitigations\n 287→\n 288→| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n 289→|------|--------|------------|------------|\n 290→| AI CLI 进程无法正常终止 | 高 | 低 | SIGTERM → SIGKILL 渐进式终止 |\n 291→| MarkdownV2 格式不兼容 | 中 | 中 | 完善测试覆盖，处理边界情况 |\n 292→| 心跳消息过多干扰用户 | 中 | 中 | 可配置频率，提供禁用选项 |\n 293→| 多会话进程管理复杂 | 中 | 低 | 使用 session-store 统一管理 |\n 294→\n 295→---\n 296→\n 297→## 10. Acceptance Criteria Summary\n 298→\n 299→- [ ] **AC-1**: 用户发送自然语言指令，Bot 调用 AI CLI 执行并将结果回传到 Telegram\n 300→- [ ] **AC-2**: AI CLI 会话上下文在多轮对话中保持，用户可连续追问\n 301→- [ ] **AC-3**: 支持通过 /stop 中断正在执行的 AI CLI 任务\n 302→- [ ] **AC-4**: 长时间运行的 AI CLI 任务有心跳进度推送，用户不会感觉卡住\n 303→- [ ] **AC-5**: AI CLI 的 Markdown 输出正确适配 Telegram MarkdownV2 格式\n 304→- [ ] **AC-6**: AI CLI 进程异常退出或超时时返回可理解的错误信息与建议操作\n 305→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3bc5266a17a3b9f417aa170e45f","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:28:17.104Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"32d57334-988b-4ab5-8989-a2e8b8385d1b","session_id":"6b971ac8-f58b-4539-b600-b41cd157b86c","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019ce3bc53d3b54334c3e3be5177933a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# Technical Implementation Plan: F-011 AI CLI Proxy\n   2→\n   3→**Feature ID**: F-011\n   4→**Feature Name**: AI CLI Proxy\n   5→**Created**: 2026-03-13\n   6→**Status**: Draft\n   7→\n   8→---\n   9→\n  10→## 1. Architecture Overview\n  11→\n  12→### 1.1 Component Diagram\n  13→\n  14→```\n  15→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  16→│                         Telegram Bot                             │\n  17→│                    (src/bot/telegram.js)                        │\n  18→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  19→                              │\n  20→                              ▼\n  21→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  22→│                      AI CLI Service                              │\n  23→│                (src/services/ai-cli-service.js)                  │\n  24→│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐     │\n  25→│  │  Process    │  │  Heartbeat   │  │  Stream             │     │\n  26→│  │  Manager    │  │  Manager     │  │  Handler            │     │\n  27→│  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘     │\n  28→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  29→         │                    │                    │\n  30→         ▼                    ▼                    ▼\n  31→┌────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐\n  32→│ Session Store  │  │ CodeBuddy       │  │ MarkdownV2           │\n  33→│ (extended)     │  │ Adapter         │  │ Formatter            │\n  34→│                │  │ (extended)      │  │                      │\n  35→└────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘\n  36→                              │\n  37→                              ▼\n  38→                    ┌─────────────────┐\n  39→                    │  CodeBuddy CLI  │\n  40→                    │  (external)     │\n  41→                    └─────────────────┘\n  42→```\n  43→\n  44→### 1.2 Key Design Decisions\n  45→\n  46→| Decision ID | Description | Rationale |\n  47→|-------------|-------------|-----------|\n  48→| D-1 | Create separate `ai-cli-service.js` instead of modifying `chat-service.js` | Separation of concerns; AI CLI execution has different lifecycle than chat |\n  49→| D-2 | Store active process info in `session-store.js` | Consistent with existing session management pattern |\n  50→| D-3 | Use SIGTERM → SIGKILL graceful termination | Standard practice, prevents zombie processes |\n  51→| D-4 | Implement MarkdownV2 formatter as pure utility | Reusable, testable, no side effects |\n  52→| D-5 | Extend `/stop` command instead of creating new `/ai-stop` | Consistent user experience with existing pattern |\n  53→\n  54→---\n  55→\n  56→## 2. Component Design\n  57→\n  58→### 2.1 AI CLI Service (`src/services/ai-cli-service.js`)\n  59→\n  60→**Purpose**: Encapsulate AI CLI execution logic with process tracking, heartbeat, and interrupt support.\n  61→\n  62→**Responsibilities**:\n  63→- Execute CodeBuddy CLI with session context\n  64→- Track active processes per session\n  65→- Provide interrupt capability\n  66→- Manage heartbeat progress notifications\n  67→- Format and return results\n  68→\n  69→**Dependencies**:\n  70→- `src/adapters/codebuddy.js` (extended)\n  71→- `src/services/session-store.js` (extended)\n  72→- `src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js` (new)\n  73→- `src/config.js`\n  74→\n  75→**Interface**:\n  76→```javascript\n  77→/**\n  78→ * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n  79→ * @property {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n  80→ * @property {string} prompt - User prompt/input\n  81→ * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n  82→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback (text: string) => void\n  83→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback (info: HeartbeatInfo) => void\n  84→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (status: string) => void\n  85→ * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Optional abort signal\n  86→ */\n  87→\n  88→/**\n  89→ * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionResult\n  90→ * @property {string} output - Final output text\n  91→ * @property {boolean} timedOut - Whether execution timed out\n  92→ * @property {boolean} interrupted - Whether execution was interrupted\n  93→ * @property {number} elapsedMs - Execution time in milliseconds\n  94→ * @property {number} exitCode - Process exit code (if completed)\n  95→ */\n  96→\n  97→/**\n  98→ * @typedef {Object} HeartbeatInfo\n  99→ * @property {number} elapsedMs - Elapsed time in milliseconds\n 100→ * @property {number} stdoutBytes - Bytes received so far\n 101→ * @property {string} status - Current status ('running', 'streaming')\n 102→ */\n 103→\n 104→/**\n 105→ * Execute AI CLI with session context and process tracking.\n 106→ * @param {AiCliExecutionOptions} options\n 107→ * @returns {Promise<AiCliExecutionResult>}\n 108→ */\n 109→export async function executeAiCli(options) {}\n 110→\n 111→/**\n 112→ * Interrupt running AI CLI task for a session.\n 113→ * @param {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n 114→ * @returns {{ ok: boolean, pid?: number, error?: string }}\n 115→ */\n 116→export function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {}\n 117→\n 118→/**\n 119→ * Check if AI CLI is running for a session.\n 120→ * @param {string} sessionId\n 121→ * @returns {boolean}\n 122→ */\n 123→export function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {}\n 124→\n 125→/**\n 126→ * Get active process info for a session.\n 127→ * @param {string} sessionId\n 128→ * @returns {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number } | null}\n 129→ */\n 130→export function getActiveProcessInfo(sessionId) {}\n 131→```\n 132→\n 133→### 2.2 CodeBuddy Adapter Extensions (`src/adapters/codebuddy.js`)\n 134→\n 135→**Changes**:\n 136→- Add `AbortSignal` support for cancellation\n 137→- Return child process reference for external management\n 138→- Expose process info (PID) during execution\n 139→\n 140→**Extended Interface**:\n 141→```javascript\n 142→/**\n 143→ * @typedef {Object} CodeBuddyOptions\n 144→ * @property {Function} [onStdoutChunk] - Stream chunk callback\n 145→ * @property {Function} [onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback\n 146→ * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Abort signal for cancellation\n 147→ * @property {Object} [processTracker] - Object to receive process reference\n 148→ */\n 149→\n 150→/**\n 151→ * @typedef {Object} CodeBuddyResult\n 152→ * @property {string} output - Output text\n 153→ * @property {number} exitCode - Exit code\n 154→ * @property {boolean} timedOut - Whether timed out\n 155→ * @property {boolean} interrupted - Whether interrupted by signal\n 156→ * @property {number} elapsedMs - Execution time\n 157→ */\n 158→\n 159→export async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n 160→  // Return extended result with process tracking\n 161→}\n 162→```\n 163→\n 164→### 2.3 MarkdownV2 Formatter (`src/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js`)\n 165→\n 166→**Purpose**: Convert Markdown output to Telegram MarkdownV2 format.\n 167→\n 168→**Interface**:\n 169→```javascript\n 170→/**\n 171→ * Characters that need escaping in MarkdownV2.\n 172→ */\n 173→const ESCAPE_CHARS = ['_', '*', '[', ']', '(', ')', '~', '`', '>', '#', '+', '-', '=', '|', '{', '}', '.', '!'];\n 174→\n 175→/**\n 176→ * Escape text for Telegram MarkdownV2 format.\n 177→ * @param {string} text - Text to escape\n 178→ * @returns {string} Escaped text\n 179→ */\n 180→export function escapeMarkdownV2(text) {\n 181→  // Escape all special characters\n 182→}\n 183→\n 184→/**\n 185→ * Format code block for Telegram MarkdownV2.\n 186→ * @param {string} code - Code content\n 187→ * @param {string} [language] - Optional language identifier\n 188→ * @returns {string} Formatted code block\n 189→ */\n 190→export function formatCodeBlock(code, language = '') {\n 191→  // ```language\\ncode\\n```\n 192→  // Note: Inside code blocks, only ` and \\ need escaping\n 193→}\n 194→\n 195→/**\n 196→ * Convert common Markdown to MarkdownV2.\n 197→ * Handles: code blocks, inline code, bold, italic, links.\n 198→ * @param {string} markdown - Input markdown\n 199→ * @returns {string} MarkdownV2 formatted text\n 200→ */\n 201→export function convertToMarkdownV2(markdown) {\n 202→  // Parse and convert each element\n 203→}\n 204→\n 205→/**\n 206→ * Split text into segments respecting code block boundaries.\n 207→ * Useful for splitting long messages.\n 208→ * @param {string} text - Text to split\n 209→ * @param {number} maxLength - Maximum length per segment\n 210→ * @returns {string[]} Array of segments\n 211→ */\n 212→export function splitRespectingCodeBlocks(text, maxLength = 4000) {}\n 213→```\n 214→\n 215→### 2.4 Session Store Extensions (`src/services/session-store.js`)\n 216→\n 217→**New Fields**:\n 218→```javascript\n 219→class SessionStore {\n 220→  // ... existing fields ...\n 221→  \n 222→  /**\n 223→   * Active AI CLI process tracking.\n 224→   * Map<sessionKey, ProcessInfo>\n 225→   * @type {Map<string, { pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number, childProcess: ChildProcess }>}\n 226→   */\n 227→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n 228→}\n 229→```\n 230→\n 231→**New Methods**:\n 232→```javascript\n 233→/**\n 234→ * Get active AI CLI process info.\n 235→ * @param {string} sessionKey\n 236→ * @returns {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, stdoutBytes: number, childProcess: ChildProcess } | null}\n 237→ */\n 238→getActiveProcess(sessionKey) {}\n 239→\n 240→/**\n 241→ * Set active AI CLI process.\n 242→ * @param {string} sessionKey\n 243→ * @param {{ pid: number, startedAt: number, childProcess: ChildProcess }} info\n 244→ */\n 245→setActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) {}\n 246→\n 247→/**\n 248→ * Update stdout bytes for active process.\n 249→ * @param {string} sessionKey\n 250→ * @param {number} bytes\n 251→ */\n 252→updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) {}\n 253→\n 254→/**\n 255→ * Clear active process.\n 256→ * @param {string} sessionKey\n 257→ */\n 258→clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {}\n 259→```\n 260→\n 261→---\n 262→\n 263→## 3. Interface Design\n 264→\n 265→### 3.1 Config Schema Extensions\n 266→\n 267→**File**: `src/config.js`\n 268→\n 269→**New Environment Variables**:\n 270→```javascript\n 271→// Add to schema\n 272→const schema = z.object({\n 273→  // ... existing fields ...\n 274→  \n 275→  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n 276→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(10000),\n 277→  AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS: z.coerce.number().int().nonnegative().default(30000),\n 278→  AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT: z.string().optional().default('true'),\n 279→});\n 280→\n 281→// Exported config additions\n 282→export const config = Object.freeze({\n 283→  // ... existing fields ...\n 284→  \n 285→  // F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n 286→  aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs: parsed.AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS,\n 287→  aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs: parsed.AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS,\n 288→  aiCliEnableHeartbeat: parseBoolean(parsed.AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT),\n 289→});\n 290→```\n 291→\n 292→### 3.2 Telegram Bot Integration\n 293→\n 294→**File**: `src/bot/telegram.js`\n 295→\n 296→**Changes to text message handler**:\n 297→```javascript\n 298→// In bot.on('text', ...) handler\n 299→\n 300→// Check if AI CLI is running for this session\n 301→if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n 302→  await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n 303→  return;\n 304→}\n 305→\n 306→// Use ai-cli-service for execution\n 307→const result = await executeAiCli({\n 308→  sessionId,\n 309→  prompt: ctx.message.text,\n 310→  hooks: {\n 311→    onChunk: (text) => streamPublisher.push(text),\n 312→    onHeartbeat: (info) => {\n 313→      // Push heartbeat progress to user\n 314→      ctx.reply(`⏳ 任务执行中... (${Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000)}s)`)\n 315→        .catch(() => {});\n 316→    },\n 317→    onStatus: (status) => {\n 318→      if (status === 'running') {\n 319→        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n 320→      }\n 321→    }\n 322→  }\n 323→});\n 324→\n 325→// Format output with MarkdownV2\n 326→const formattedOutput = convertToMarkdownV2(result.output);\n 327→\n 328→// Handle result\n 329→if (result.interrupted) {\n 330→  await ctx.reply('⏹️ 任务已被中断。');\n 331→} else if (result.timedOut) {\n 332→  await ctx.reply(`⏰ 任务执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`);\n 333→} else {\n 334→  streamPublisher.setFinalText(formattedOutput);\n 335→}\n 336→```\n 337→\n 338→### 3.3 Stop Command Extension\n 339→\n 340→**File**: `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js`\n 341→\n 342→**Changes**:\n 343→```javascript\n 344→import { interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning } from '../../../services/ai-cli-service.js';\n 345→import { stopPipeline } from '../../../services/pipeline-controller.js';\n 346→\n 347→export async function handleStop(handlerCtx) {\n 348→  const { params, reply, userId, sessionId } = handlerCtx;\n 349→  \n 350→  // First, check for AI CLI task\n 351→  if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n 352→    const result = interruptAiCli(sessionId);\n 353→    \n 354→    if (result.ok) {\n 355→      await logAuditEntry({\n 356→        userId,\n 357→        action: 'stop-ai-cli',\n 358→        params: { pid: result.pid },\n 359→        result: 'success',\n 360→        sessionId\n 361→      });\n 362→      \n 363→      await reply(`✅ AI CLI 任务已中断 (PID: ${result.pid})。`);\n 364→      return;\n 365→    } else {\n 366→      await reply(`❌ 中断失败: ${result.error}`);\n 367→      return;\n 368→    }\n 369→  }\n 370→  \n 371→  // Fall back to pipeline stop (existing logic)\n 372→  // ... existing stop pipeline code ...\n 373→}\n 374→```\n 375→\n 376→---\n 377→\n 378→## 4. Data Model\n 379→\n 380→### 4.1 Session Store Schema\n 381→\n 382→```javascript\n 383→// ProcessInfo type\n 384→{\n 385→  pid: number,           // Process ID\n 386→  startedAt: number,     // Timestamp when process started\n 387→  stdoutBytes: number,   // Bytes received so far\n 388→  childProcess: ChildProcess  // Reference to child process for termination\n 389→}\n 390→```\n 391→\n 392→### 4.2 Execution Result Schema\n 393→\n 394→```javascript\n 395→// AiCliExecutionResult\n 396→{\n 397→  output: string,        // Final output text (MarkdownV2 formatted)\n 398→  timedOut: boolean,     // True if timed out\n 399→  interrupted: boolean,  // True if interrupted by user\n 400→  elapsedMs: number,     // Total execution time\n 401→  exitCode: number | null,  // Exit code (null if interrupted)\n 402→  stderr: string         // Error output if any\n 403→}\n 404→```\n 405→\n 406→### 4.3 Heartbeat Info Schema\n 407→\n 408→```javascript\n 409→// HeartbeatInfo\n 410→{\n 411→  elapsedMs: number,     // Elapsed time in ms\n 412→  stdoutBytes: number,   // Bytes received\n 413→  status: 'running' | 'streaming' | 'waiting'\n 414→}\n 415→```\n 416→\n 417→---\n 418→\n 419→## 5. Test Strategy\n 420→\n 421→### 5.1 Unit Tests\n 422→\n 423→**File**: `tests/services/ai-cli-service.test.js`\n 424→```javascript\n 425→describe('AiCliService', () => {\n 426→  describe('executeAiCli', () => {\n 427→    it('should execute CodeBuddy and return output');\n 428→    it('should track active process in session store');\n 429→    it('should call onChunk callback for streaming output');\n 430→    it('should call onHeartbeat callback periodically');\n 431→    it('should handle timeout correctly');\n 432→    it('should handle abort signal');\n 433→    it('should clean up process on completion');\n 434→  });\n 435→  \n 436→  describe('interruptAiCli', () => {\n 437→    it('should interrupt running process');\n 438→    it('should return error if no process running');\n 439→    it('should clean up session store after interrupt');\n 440→  });\n 441→  \n 442→  describe('isAiCliRunning', () => {\n 443→    it('should return true when process is active');\n 444→    it('should return false when no process');\n 445→  });\n 446→});\n 447→```\n 448→\n 449→**File**: `tests/utils/markdown-v2-formatter.test.js`\n 450→```javascript\n 451→describe('MarkdownV2Formatter', () => {\n 452→  describe('escapeMarkdownV2', () => {\n 453→    it('should escape all special characters');\n 454→    it('should handle empty string');\n 455→    it('should handle text with no special chars');\n 456→    it('should handle text with multiple special chars');\n 457→  });\n 458→  \n 459→  describe('formatCodeBlock', () => {\n 460→    it('should format code block without language');\n 461→    it('should format code block with language');\n 462→    it('should escape backticks inside code');\n 463→  });\n 464→  \n 465→  describe('convertToMarkdownV2', () => {\n 466→    it('should convert code blocks');\n 467→    it('should convert inline code');\n 468→    it('should convert bold text');\n 469→    it('should convert italic text');\n 470→    it('should convert links');\n 471→    it('should handle nested formatting');\n 472→    it('should preserve line breaks');\n 473→  });\n 474→  \n 475→  describe('splitRespectingCodeBlocks', () => {\n 476→    it('should not split inside code blocks');\n 477→    it('should split at paragraph boundaries');\n 478→    it('should respect maxLength');\n 479→  });\n 480→});\n 481→```\n 482→\n 483→### 5.2 Integration Tests\n 484→\n 485→**File**: `tests/integration/ai-cli-integration.test.js`\n 486→```javascript\n 487→describe('AI CLI Integration', () => {\n 488→  it('should execute full flow: prompt → execute → stream → result');\n 489→  it('should maintain context across multiple turns');\n 490→  it('should handle /stop during execution');\n 491→  it('should show heartbeat progress');\n 492→  it('should format output correctly for Telegram');\n 493→});\n 494→```\n 495→\n 496→### 5.3 Test Helpers\n 497→\n 498→**File**: `tests/helpers/mock-codebuddy.js`\n 499→```javascript\n 500→/**\n 501→ * Mock CodeBuddy CLI for testing.\n 502→ * Simulates various scenarios: success, timeout, error, slow output.\n 503→ */\n 504→export function createMockCodeBuddy(options = {}) {\n 505→  return {\n 506→    simulateSuccess: (output) => { ... },\n 507→    simulateTimeout: () => { ... },\n 508→    simulateError: (exitCode, stderr) => { ... },\n 509→    simulateSlowOutput: (chunks, interval) => { ... },\n 510→  };\n 511→}\n 512→```\n 513→\n 514→---\n 515→\n 516→## 6. Implementation Phases\n 517→\n 518→### Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n 519→- Add config fields\n 520→- Create MarkdownV2 formatter utility\n 521→- Extend session store with process tracking\n 522→\n 523→### Phase 2: Core Service (T-010 ~ T-029)\n 524→- Create AI CLI service\n 525→- Extend CodeBuddy adapter\n 526→- Implement process tracking\n 527→\n 528→### Phase 3: Integration (T-030 ~ T-049)\n 529→- Integrate with Telegram bot\n 530→- Extend /stop command\n 531→- Add heartbeat progress\n 532→\n 533→### Phase 4: Testing & Polish (T-050 ~ T-069)\n 534→- Unit tests\n 535→- Integration tests\n 536→- Error handling refinement\n 537→\n 538→---\n 539→\n 540→## 7. Risk Assessment\n 541→\n 542→| Risk ID | Description | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n 543→|---------|-------------|--------|------------|------------|\n 544→| R-1 | Process becomes zombie after SIGTERM | High | Low | Implement SIGKILL after grace period (5s) |\n 545→| R-2 | MarkdownV2 formatting breaks existing output | Medium | Medium | Comprehensive test suite, gradual rollout |\n 546→| R-3 | Heartbeat messages spam user | Medium | Medium | Configurable interval, minimum 10s |\n 547→| R-4 | Race condition in process tracking | High | Low | Use chat-queue for serialization |\n 548→| R-5 | Memory leak from unreleased process refs | Medium | Low | Cleanup on process close, timeout, and session reset |\n 549→\n 550→---\n 551→\n 552→## 8. Rollback Plan\n 553→\n 554→If issues arise:\n 555→1. **Feature flag**: Set `AI_CLI_ENABLE_HEARTBEAT=false` to disable heartbeat\n 556→2. **Fallback to chat-service**: The existing `chat-service.js` remains unchanged, can be used if needed\n 557→3. **Process cleanup**: On restart, all tracked processes are cleared\n 558→\n 559→---\n 560→\n 561→## 9. Monitoring & Observability\n 562→\n 563→### 9.1 Metrics to Track\n 564→- AI CLI execution duration (histogram)\n 565→- AI CLI success/failure rate\n 566→- Heartbeat delivery rate\n 567→- Process interrupt frequency\n 568→- Output size distribution\n 569→\n 570→### 9.2 Logging\n 571→- Log process start with PID, sessionId, prompt length\n 572→- Log process end with exit code, duration, output size\n 573→- Log interrupts with reason\n 574→- Log heartbeat events at debug level\n 575→\n 576→---\n 577→\n 578→## 10. Documentation Updates\n 579→\n 580→### 10.1 Files to Update\n 581→- `.prizm-docs/runtime.prizm`: Add F-011 entries to KEY_FILES, TRAPS, DECISIONS\n 582→- `README.md`: Document new config options\n 583→- `.env.example`: Add new environment variables\n 584→\n 585→### 10.2 New Documentation\n 586→- `docs/ai-cli-proxy.md`: Feature documentation for users\n 587→\n 588→---\n 589→\n 590→## 11. User Story Mapping\n 591→\n 592→| User Story | Tasks |\n 593→|------------|-------|\n 594→| US-1: Natural Language Execution | T-010, T-011, T-012, T-030, T-031 |\n 595→| US-2: Multi-turn Context | T-013 (uses existing session-store) |\n 596→| US-3: Task Interrupt | T-014, T-015, T-032, T-033 |\n 597→| US-4: Heartbeat Progress | T-004, T-016, T-034 |\n 598→| US-5: Error Handling | T-017, T-035 |\n 599→| US-6: Markdown Formatting | T-006, T-007, T-008, T-036 |\n 600→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019ce3bc53d3b54334c3e3be5177933a","__timestamp":"2026-03-12T20:28:17.107Z","_requestId":"39750009e8f3457a8b44aaadfd2ecc82"}
